title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl until well blended.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator until ready to use. Excellent served with carrots, cauliflower, celery, broccoli, etc.

title: cowboy rice
directions: Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 325°.
Serves around 6.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Mix altogether and pour over medium head of grated cabbage with a 1/2 of small onion.
Some may like more sugar and vinegar. This recipe can also be frozen.

title: peanut butter breakfast bars
directions: Line 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil and coat foil with nonstick spray.

title: texas pinto beans
directions: Wash beans; cook 1 1/2 hours with Streak-O-Lean.
Brown ground round and drain.
Add to pinto beans.
Chop onion, bell pepper and jalapeno pepper.
Add this plus tomatoes, garlic powder, salt and pepper to beans.
Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: champagne punch
directions: Pour all
into large punch bowl and mix.
Add ice cubes or ice ring.

title: perfect spaghetti
directions: Mix ingredients together in a crock-pot and cook on high for 30 to 45 minutes, then simmer on low from 2 to 5 hours.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (use 325° if using glass dish). Reserving 1 tablespoon for garnish, pat coconut on bottom of buttered 9 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and butter; beat until smooth.
Stir in flour and salt.
In small bowl, beat egg whites to soft peaks; fold into sweetened condensed milk mixture and turn into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put uncooked pork chops on bottom of baking dish.
Add onions and potatoes.
Pour soup and milk over these layers.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Delicious served over fresh strawberries.
Freezes well!

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Blend well with mixer.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix, then shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 90 to 96 cookies.

title: cherry cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add lemon juice, cream cheese, salt and salad dressing.
Blend thoroughly with mixer. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Whip until fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: virginia's party rye bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients all together and spread on party rye bread slices.
Sprinkle with bacon pieces on top and put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Bring to boil 1 cup sour milk (2 tablespoons vinegar and the remainder milk).
Stir shortening, sugar, salt and baking soda into milk.
Cool.
Add 1 egg and 1 package dry yeast.
Stir in 3 cups sifted flour.
Let rise 20 minutes, then roll out in a rectangle.
Butter half and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Fold over like a sandwich and cut into 1/2-inch strips about 3 inches long. Twist strips and bake on greased cookie sheets 12 minutes at 375°. Frost with icing while hot.

title: jersey fresh taffy apple dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together cream cheese and brown sugar. Add vanilla and peanuts.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: spanish noodle casserole
directions: Cook 1/2 large package noodles in salted water for 20 minutes. Drain and rinse with hot water.
Fry 1 pound hamburger and 1 medium onion (chopped) until brown and crumbly.
Add to noodles tomatoes, corn, black olives (pitted), garlic, salt and black pepper.
Add meat, onions and grated cheese.
Place mixture in a greased baking dish; cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on one large cookie sheet and bake per package instructions.
Cool.
Beat the cream cheese, sour cream and dry dressing mix together until smooth.
Spread filling over cooled biscuit base and top with fresh, finely chopped veggies. Top with finely shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: syrup
directions: Stir together syrup, sugar, water and salt in a saucepan and slowly bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Let boil for 6 to 7 minutes.
Add maple flavoring to taste.
Makes little over a pint.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar, nuts and milk.
Bake at 350°.
Turn batter into a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over batter.
Pour boiling water over chocolate chips and let stand 1 to 2 minutes until chocolate melts, then stir.
Pour over batter.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to cool.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: In the bottom of a 9x13 pan place one layer of graham crackers. Beat vanilla pudding with 3 cups of milk, mix in frozen cool whip. Spread half of mixture on layer of crackers. Put another layer of graham crackers in pan. Top with remaining pudding. Add another layer of crackers. Mix frosting with 3 tsp. milk. Spread over top of crackers. Refrigerate 12-24 hours. This can also be frozen.

title: smoked sausage harvest casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add cabbage, onions and carrots.
Saute 5 minutes.
Stir in beans, tomatoes and vinegar.
Sprinkle cheese, flour and pepper over cabbage mixture. Spoon into greased 2-quart dish.
Cut sausage into serving pieces. Arrange on top of cabbage; push down partially.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, salt and syrup in 2-quart dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes more, stirring after 3 minutes.
Continue until syrup and peanuts are highly browned.
Stir in oleo, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Spread on well-buttered, large cookie sheet and cool. When cooled, break into pieces.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
If using canned carrots, use liquid as part of the water amount.
If using fresh carrots, cook separately until tender.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: creamed corn
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, butter and onion salt in medium saucepan over low heat until cheese melts.
Add drained corn. Cook until heated through.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan. Stir in meat, garlic and onion, cooking until meat is no longer pink. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce flame and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cookie crust for pies
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar thoroughly.
Add butter and mix until dough forms.
Press into 9-inch pie pan with fingers and form fluted rim.
Prick holes in crust with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: mark's teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix together and marinate overnight.
Good on venison.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip in large mixing bowl until smooth.
Divide mixture between pie crusts and top with cherry pie filling.
May be sprinkled with graham cracker crumbs or pecans.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend well and refrigerate several hours before serving. Great with raw vegetables or chips.

title: joojeh kabob
directions: Grate the onions, keeping the juice.
Mix the onions with the lemon juice and the yogurt in a shallow pan.
Mixture should be deep enough to half cover chicken pieces.
Marinate chicken for several hours or in the refrigerator overnight.
Chicken should be turned over halfway through the marinating period.

title: cheese tortellini casserole
directions: Cook tortellini and peas according to package directions.
Cut ham into chunks.
Meanwhile, prepare cheese sauce as follows:

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt margarine, add cocoa and water and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared large jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 22 minutes. Frost while hot with Texas Sheet Cake Frosting.

title: red potato salad
directions: Whisk together mustard, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add sugar. Gently stir potatoes, tomato, bacon and chives into mustard mixture.
Store, covered in refrigerator for up to 2 days.
Stir in additional mayonnaise to moisten if necessary.
Serves 12.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together except the peppers. Stuff the mixture into the peppers and place in a roaster.
Mix water with leftover parts of catsup in can and pour in roaster for gravy.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sherbet ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and place in freezer.
Let stand 2 hours.
Remove from freezer and stir slushy mixture.
Place back in freezer for 6 hours.
Serve.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil rice.
In large greased casserole, place sliced carrots, rice, potatoes, then 1/2 onion, ground beef and rest of onion.
Top with tomato soup which has been mixed with water.
Cover with lid or foil and bake 1 1/2 or 2 hours.
Serve with tossed salad and rolls.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar; let stand one hour.
Combine eggs and sugars; add to mustard sauce.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Cool before serving.
Add Miracle Whip for a milder sauce.
Serve with pretzels, cheese slices, Fritos or on sandwiches.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook rice and broccoli according to directions on package. Drain in colander.
Use only a sprinkle of salt in water to cook rice.
No salt in broccoli.
The butter and Cheez Whiz are so salty; additional salt is unnecessary.

title: tempo tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; chill for several hours before using.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread cream cheese mixture on crust.
Grate carrots, broccoli, celery, cauliflower and Cheddar cheese on top.
Refrigerate.

title: ham and swiss party rolls
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Layer bottom of rolls with ham and cheese.
Put tops of rolls back on.
Mix melted butter and other ingredients.
Pour slowly over rolls.
(Can use pastry brush.)
Put rolls back in package.
Set aside for five hours or overnight. This also freezes well.
Heat in 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice into smaller pieces if desired.

title: chicken breast with peanuts
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper (and salt to taste).
Brown lightly in olive oil.
Remove from pan.
Add shallot, onion and pepper.
Saute as desired (from just clear to browned).
Add wine, stir in chile garlic paste.
Return chicken to pan, cover, cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Add peanuts or almonds, cook 5 to 10 minutes more.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in Kraft Italian dressing.
Toss apple in lemon juice and add with remaining ingredients to chicken.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and 1/4 cup chopped onion.
Drain fat.
Add 1 can tomato sauce, taco mix and water.
Cook 1 minute.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Rinse and drain beans.
Layer over meat.
Pour tomatoes and chillies over beans.
Pour hash browns over the top and sprinkle green pepper and rest of onion over potatoes.
Mix cheese soup, milk, sugar and Worcestershire sauce and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together to form a crust.
Place in a 9 x 12 x 3-inch pan, using a fork.

title: lemon snowflake cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 13 to 16 minutes.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and congeal.
Top with:

title: basil mayonnaise
directions: Blend first five ingredients in blender until fine.
Add this mixture to the mayonnaise.
A good dip for raw vegetables.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown the meat; add pepper, onion, tomato paste, salt, green pepper and oregano.
Fill the pie shell with the meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.
Add 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes more (until melted).

title: quick mix apple-nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan. In a medium bowl, combine Quick Mix, sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Mix well.
Add eggs and milk or water.
Blend well for 1 minute. Add apples; blend 2 more minutes.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour in prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes, until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients and beat well.
Put this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix and nuts evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a Baggie.
Moisten potatoes with water.
Shake a few pieces at a time in mixture. Place in buttered pan. Bake for 1 hour at 375°; turn after the first 30 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, sprinkle on shredded cheese.

title: unforgettable cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
While cake is cooking, in a small saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer.
When cake is done, make holes all over the top and pour the pineapple and sugar mixture over it.
Mix pudding according to the box directions.
When thickened, add coconut and spread over cake.
Next, spread Cool Whip over top of pudding and sprinkle with nuts.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine water and Minute rice and set aside.
Cut up and stir together apples, grapes, pineapple, oranges and sugar.
Whip together the whipping cream and sugar until stiff peaks form. Stir in vanilla and mini marshmallows.
Combine rice, fruit mixture and whipping cream mixture.
Refrigerate.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Blend the pudding and milk together until thick.
Add the Cool Whip to the pudding.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers (do not smash).
Add 1/2 pudding mixture on top of crackers, then another layer of crackers, then the last 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.

title: mom's chicken supreme
directions: Grease a casserole dish well.
Spread rice on bottom and add water.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Combine soups and parsley. Spread on top of chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours. Yield:
8 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in shortening.
Meanwhile, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk and sugar to yeast mixture.
Then add flour.
Mix well and put in the refrigerator in closed bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
If necessary, add more flour to make soft dough. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks using only portion needed.
May be used for bread at any meal. Stuff with ham.
You can add raisins, sugar and cinnamon for sweet buns.

title: no-fat creamy new york cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Moisten fingers with water and press cookie crumbs over bottom and slightly up sides of 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Chill while preparing remaining ingredients. With a rotary beater or hand mixer, beat yogurt, honey, vanilla, arrowroot and egg whites until thoroughly blended.
Pour filling into crumb-lined pan.
Bake at 300° for 60 to 75 minutes until center is set and surface is lightly browned.
Remove from oven, cool to room temperature and refrigerate until chilled through.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick the pie crust with fork and bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°. Cover bottom of pie crust with two layers of tomato slices. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and half the oregano and onion. Repeat layers.
Combine Cheddar cheese and mayonnaise and spread over pie.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, celery and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, olives, water and chili powder.
Layer in casserole buttered taco shells, sauce, grated sharp cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat, using up to 12 taco sheets; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; strain well.
Add soups and sour cream.
Mix well.
Top with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: miracle chocolate cake
directions: Mix thoroughly salad dressing and sugar.
Sift next 4 ingredients.
Add alternately with 1 cup water.
When thoroughly mixed, add vanilla.
Beat approximately 2 minutes.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into 2 cake pans lined with wax paper or 1 sheet pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
Handle carefully.
Frost with Soft Chocolate Frosting.

title: good beef stew
directions: Dip beef in flour.
Brown in oil or bacon grease.
Boil floured beef in water, about 1 hour.
Add all vegetables, except peas.
Continue to boil until tender.
Add peas and simmer 7-10 minutes.

title: good 'n' fillin'
directions: Cook sausage, onions and green peppers over medium heat in 1 tablespoon oil until veggies are tender and sausage is done. Stir in tomatoes and peas; reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Blend in sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flavorings.
Beat in flour just until smooth, no longer.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
(I use sugar to coat pan instead of flour; it gives a nice crust.)
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: flag dessert
directions: Slice 1 cup of the strawberries; set aside.
Halve remaining strawberries; set aside.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients together.
Form ball. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy fresh peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1/2 cup sugar.
Let stand for 30 minutes or until juice forms.
Melt butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Make batter out of remaining ingredients.
Pour batter over butter, then pour fruit and juice over batter.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cowboy food
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add beans and tomatoes. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine; when tender, add flour, salt, mustard and Tabasco.
Gradually add milk and cook until consistency of white sauce.
Add cheese, seasoned salt, mushrooms, pimentos and olives.
Rinse hominy in cold water; drain well.
Mix hominy with sauce and place in lightly buttered casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until hot.
This can be made the day or night before and it can be served hot or cold.

and

minutes.
When
done, remove from oven and
spread jar of marshmallow cream over top of cake.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Then prepare frosting.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix
vegetables
together.
Pour
oil over; mix and let stand. Mix vinegar, water, sugar and salt in pan and bring to a
boil. Remove
from
stove and add lemon jello.
Stir until dissolved. Let
cool.	Pour over vegetables and mix together. Add celery seed.
Can be kept 2 to 3 weeks.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: chocolate peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in pan; boil for a couple minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and salt.
Put in greased square pan and refrigerate, then cut into squares when chilled.

title: baked steak
directions: Mix salt, pepper and flour.
Roll cut steak pieces in mixture. Add onion to steak pieces and put in frypan; brown nicely.
Put meat in a 2-quart casserole.
Put soup and water in frypan and stir until all residue from meat is mixed with liquid.
Pour mixture over meat in casserole and cover tightly.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Finely chop stems, onions and peppers.
In large skillet with 3 tablespoons butter, saute stems, onions and peppers.
Cook for 5 minutes over medium heat. Add bread crumbs and spices to skillet mixture.
Stir together; remove from heat.
Put 1 teaspoon of mixture in each mushroom cap. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Pat fruit dry with paper towel and arrange in 12 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Melt butter in 2-quart pan over low heat. Stir in brown sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Remove from heat and spoon over fruit.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in small amount of salted water until tender; drain. Put in casserole dish. Add cream of mushroom soup, diluted with 1/2 can milk. Mix in onion rings and sprinkle few rings on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked cheese puffs(makes 60 puffs)
directions: Note:
Can be frozen and baked later.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large stockpot; cover with water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes or until done.
Reserve broth for stew.
When chicken is cool, remove skin, debone and cut into bite sized pieces.
Defat stock.
In a large skillet, place browned ground beef and onions. Cook until onions are transparent.
In a large stockpot, combine chicken, ground beef mixture and all of the other ingredients except corn.
Cook over low heat for several hours.
Best if simmered all day, stirring occasionally.
During the last hour of cooking, add creamed corn.
Yields 8 quarts.
Great to freeze in a quantity which fits your family.

title: christmas rainbow
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed on package, baking in two well-greased and floured 9-inch layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes; poke with fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Do not remove from pans.

title: spaniard special
directions: Brown meat; add green pepper.
Cook until tender; stir in seasoning mix, tomatoes and noodles.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or longer.
Serves 4.

title: best "machine" bread
directions: Mix cracked wheat and boiling water.
Use plastic spoon to stir.
Add butter, oil and honey.
Allow mixture to cool to warm. Add remaining ingredients.
(Have all ingredients at room temperature and use level measurements.)
Use 2 1/2 to 3 hours on bread machine.

title: chili con casa
directions: Mix and put into crock-pot.
Heat and serve with nacho chips.

title: mediterranean lamb broil
directions: Broil chops 5 minutes; season with salt and pepper.
Turn and broil 5 minutes longer.
Season with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, in large skillet, slowly cook zucchini, onion, pepper and garlic in butter.
Sprinkle basil, 1/2 teaspoon salt and marjoram over vegetables.
Cover and cook 4 more minutes or until tender.
Serve lamb chops and vegetables over linguini, if desired.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and cream cheese.
Add sugar, eggs (one at a time), cake flour and vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: poppy seed bread or muffins
directions: Mix cake mix, butterscotch pudding and water together.
Add eggs, melted butter and poppy seed.
Bake 30 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 375°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1/4 to 1/3 cup mix to one mug of hot water.
Store in a big airtight container.
Great for camping trips.
Serves 36.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook for two hours, adding water to your liking.
Add 2 cups rice 1/2 hour before serving.
(Can be served over the rice, if preferred.)

title: apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and brown sugar and put in microwave for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Then add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/4 cup 10x sugar.
Mix well and serve with sliced apples.
For a party, dip apples in pineapple or lemon juice to keep from turning brown.

title: whole wheat popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Generously coat 6 large or 8 small metal or glass muffin molds with vegetable cooking spray.
In a food processor, blender, electric mixer or by hand, combine the ingredients.
Mix or stir until the batter is smooth.
Place the sprayed muffin molds in the oven to preheat for 2 minutes.
Pour the batter into the preheated cups, filling 2/3 full, and return to the oven.
Bake in top third of the oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in processor.
Put 1/2 mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine softened cream cheese and margarine.
Stir in 16 ounces Cool Whip.
In a 2nd bowl, stir up pudding, milk and vanilla.
Add to 1st bowl and blend completely. Spread over cookies in pan and top with remaining cookies. Refrigerate.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Put butter and onion in 3-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Nuke, uncovered, on High for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper, then milk and broth.
Cover and nuke on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Squeeze out extra moisture from broccoli and add to soup.
Cover and nuke 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar with shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Chill 1 hour, then roll in balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture (2 tablespoons cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: celery seed crackers
directions: Beat egg until light and frothy. Add milk and oil; beat well combine flour, celery seeds, and salt; add to egg mixture, stirring well. Chill dough at least 2 hours. Roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface, and cut with assorted 1 1/2 inch canap cutters. Place on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine; add pepper.
Cook until golden brown.
Add flour and cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat. Add broth, water and bay leaf.
Cook for 40 minutes and remove bay leaf.
Place soup into individual soup bowls.
Toast bread, place into bowls and sprinkle cheese on top.
Place soup bowls in oven at 425° until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs, milk and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake in an oblong pan or baking dish.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator.

title: blueberry delight
directions: *Any fresh or frozen fruit can be used in place of blueberries.

title: john's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean
mushrooms
and
break stems out carefully.
Drop mushroom caps into boiling water for about 2 minutes and drain and cool.
Mix
onion,
crackers and 1/4 cup of cheese into a paste. Fill
mushroom
caps with filling.	Top with remaining cheese. Bake
at
low
heat
until cheese melts, abut 275° to 300°. Enjoy.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef in skillet which has been sprinkled with salt.
Add onions and peppers.
Brown.
Drain excess fat.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: crab bisque(a delicious cream soup)
directions: In a heavy stockpot, melt the butter over medium heat. Add chicken stock, stirring until well blended. Add flour and stir until well blended and mixture begins to bubble. Add milk, salt, the half and half, white pepper and dried parsley. Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth; boil for 2 minutes. Gently add crabmeat and heat until mixture begins to simmer. Serve hot. Makes 12 servings. Preparation time: 0:30.

title: chicken on a cloud
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Using whisk, beat eggs, milk and melted butter in bowl.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and pepper and gradually add to egg mixture, beating until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup parsley.
Refrigerate batter until needed.
Rub chicken pieces with smashed garlic.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in skillet over medium heat.
When light brown, add chicken, skin side down.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes each side.
Turn pieces, skin side up.
Pour batter over chicken.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until chicken is cooked and "cloud" is puffed and brown.
Sprinkle with additional parsley to serve.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries, reserve juice and add water to make 2 cups. Bring juice and water to a boil; stir in jello until dissolved. Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: crisp topped asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and save liquid.
In a skillet, melt margarine and stir in flour until smooth.
Slowly add asparagus liquid.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
In a greased baking dish, sprinkle 1/2 the crumbs and cover with 1/2 sauce.
Place all asparagus spears, followed by all egg slices.
Top with remaining sauce. Cover with cracker crumbs dotted with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pickled sugar snap peas
directions: Note:
Use quart canning jars or a crock.
Do not use metal or plastic.
A two layer (inner-cheesecloth; outer plastic wrap) cap will work for a cover, if needed.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Bring to a full boil (stir). Boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Let cool.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend cheese to spreading consistency with milk.
Add crabmeat, onion and horseradish and blend well.
Heat at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet, along with onion, salt, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Drain liquid from vegetables. Spread meat mixture in bottom of an oiled 3-quart baking dish. Combine drained vegetables and spread over meat layer.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Slowly add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks; stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes.
Cool; add butter and vanilla.
Line bottom and sides of square Pyrex 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with vanilla wafers; spread 1/3 of pudding over the wafers and top with layer of sliced bananas.
Continue to layer wafers, pudding and bananas, ending with last 1/3 of pudding.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time. Spoon on top of pudding, spreading to cover entire surface and sealing well to edges.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until delicately brown.
When serving a large group, increase amounts and use a punch bowl.
Omit meringue and sprinkle wafer crumbs on top.

title: sheet oats cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and continue creaming.
Add eggs, salt, vanilla, flour and oats.
Mix well.
Pour into two greased and floured cookie sheets 10 1/2 x 15 1/2.
Spread evenly and bake 350° about 20 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Pour into baking pie dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, juice and Sweet 'N Low.
Stir in cabbage and pineapple.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Crush
crackers
and add
salt.
Dip
chicken
on
both sides; place in baking
dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Put about 1 tablespoon of spaghetti sauce on each.
Bake until almost done at 350° for
35 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese on top of each portion and bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs, beaten well. Add flour, nuts and Hershey's syrup.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° (in glass 325°) for 30 to 35 minutes. While warm, cover with miniature marshmallows.

title: shelba's cheese dip
directions: Mix and melt in microwave or double boiler.
May add milk to thin.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: In large bowl, mix cream cheese and peppermint flavoring until well blended.
Gradually add powdered sugar and knead on bread board or counter until no longer sticky and shapes easily into small balls.
Divide into 4 equal portions.
To each portion knead in 1 drop of food coloring of your choice or enough to make desired color.

title: applesauce-pecan cake
directions: Start with Duncan Hines spice cake mix.
Substitute a 15 ounce jar of applesauce for the water.
Fold in 1 cup chopped pecans. Bake as directed.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine sugar, allspice, cloves, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and cider in a large saucepan.
Slowly bring to boil.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve warm, garnished with orange slices.

title: raisin sauce for hams
directions: Boil raisins in water for about 5 minutes.
Add sugar, cornstarch and spices.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Blend in vinegar.
Serve hot over ham.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Layer in order, using the amounts you wish.
Chill and serve with favorite chip.

title: good potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into 1/4-inch pieces.
Cook until done.
Drain water and let cool.
Mix onion and salt.
Cut eggs into small pieces.
Mix salad dressing and relish into potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika and let set overnight for best flavor. Serves 10.

title: homemade peanut butter
directions: Note:
Peanut butter can be made easily with a food processor or blender.
The longer you blend or process the peanuts, the softer the peanut butter will be.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat and seal edges on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fossie's chicken
directions: Whip together the first 3 ingredients. Dip chicken pieces. Roll in the Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Put a little water in pan before baking at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain; set aside.
In large bowl, combine milk, eggs, dry mustard and salt.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and sausage.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, egg and butter; mix until batter is moist; do not overbeat.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Yields 12.

title: linguine a la anne
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions and drain. Return it to the pot you boiled it in.
Melt 4 tablespoons of the oleo in a saucepan.
Blend in the flour and salt, then the liquid drained from the mushrooms, water, evaporated milk and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil and stir the sauce a minute or two until it thickens.
Add 2 cups of the sauce and the drained mushrooms to the linguine and toss until well mixed.
Spoon the linguini mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, pressing it up the sides to leave a slight hollow in the center of the dish.
Toss the ham in the remaining sauce and spoon it into the hollow in the pasta. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake the uncovered casserole 20 minutes at 400°.
Meanwhile, saute the sliced peppers in the remaining oleo until soft.

title: chicken aloha
directions: In a frying pan, cook celery and pepper in butter or margarine just until tender-crisp. Add remaining ingredients except noodles. Serve over chow mein noodles and top with toasted almonds. You may add coconut if you wish.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze lemon juice into gallon jar.
Fill with room temperature water to 3/4 full.
Add sugar and stir until it dissolves.
Finish filling gallon jar with ice.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a large pan, saute onions and bell peppers until soft. Add diced tomatoes and Ro-Tel.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients and add enough flour to make soft dough.
Roll out dough and cut.
Bake at 400°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Put sugar cookie dough on a pizza pan and bake according to package.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cookie crust.
Arrange fruit on top. Refrigerate.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Press into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: granola bars
directions: Note:
Substitute peanut butter for some of the margarine.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of melted margarine with graham cracker crumbs. Press in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat not less than 15 minutes:
eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar.
Spread over crumbs.
Cover with sliced bananas and well-drained pineapple. Spread with Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: aram's smile:  ice tea
directions: Prepare teas after combining in a pan and cook.
Cool.
Add honey or sugar.

title: soup mix
directions: Bring to boil.
Cool for 45 minutes.
Then pour into jars and seal.
Makes 9 to 11 quarts.
Can be cooled and frozen.

title: kisses
directions: Add salt and cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat very stiff. Beat in 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Fold in remaining sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased paper on a pan.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 5 minutes. Turn up to brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, tear tortillas and layer with chicken. Layer onions and layer cheese.
Repeat layers.
Pour soup and sour cream mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° to heat through. Melt a little extra cheese on top.

title: grandmas pancakes
directions: Put soda in milk then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Cook on oiled griddle.

title: marinade for chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best if marinated overnight.

title: chicken n' cheese rolls
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken pieces.
Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place a slice of cheese on top of each chicken piece. Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Dilute mayonnaise with milk in a small bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together in another bowl. Dip chicken rolls in mayonnaise mixture, then roll in crumb mixture, covering completely.
Place chicken rolls in lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Add water. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 2 minutes. Stir in milk; heat through but do not boil.
Stir in vanilla. Just before serving, beat with hand beater until foaming or stir until smooth.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and eggs.
Add butter, pecans and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift all the dry ingredients and make a well in the center of the dry ingredients.
Combine milk, oil and eggs.
Pour into the center of the dry ingredients. Add bananas.
Stir mixture until moist (do not overmix).
Spoon into two greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cream until firm and set aside.
Whip the next 4 ingredients.
Fold whipped cream into mixture.
Spread into crust. Pour pie filling over top.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over crust.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over top and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares and serve.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese, lemon juice and mayonnaise until smooth.
Whip the cream, adding sugar.
Mix with cheese mixture; add fruit and nuts.
Dice cranberry sauce and fold into mixture. Freeze and use as desired.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Break up corned beef with fork and add drained, cooked noodles and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in buttered baking dish and top with coarsely crushed cracker crumbs which have been mixed with 3 to 4 tablespoons melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake in half.
Tear half the cake in bite size pieces.
Place cake pieces in bottom of 3-quart glass bowl or trifle dish.
Drizzle with half of melted fruit spread.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Melt some
butter in a skillet and brown chicken.
Lift pieces out
into
a
flat
baking
dish.
Add chicken broth to drippings in
skillet
and
stir over low heat.
Mix flour and light cream together until smooth.
Add to chicken broth along with mustard and
stir
until
thickened.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cholesterol-free casserole
directions: Rub margarine on bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Add rice. Parboil squash, cut in slices.
Place squash over rice.
Pour corn over squash and place onions on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: baked scrambled eggs(great for brunch)
directions: Mix all the ingredients except bacon and let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Add bacon to mixture.
Grease a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix everything together.
Make walnut size balls.
Put on baking sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: edith's salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
In a bowl put Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with the jello.
Add the 2 cups of cottage cheese.
Fold together.
Then add pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pelican pub shrimp scampi
directions: *If using cooked shrimp, keep in low heat warming oven and add at the end.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix crackers with 1 cup melted butter.

title: island style chicken
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving syrup.
In skillet, brown chicken in shortening, pouring off fat.
Add reserved syrup, broth, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover; cook over low heat for 40 minutes.
Add green pepper and pineapple chunks; cook 5 minutes more or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Combine cornstarch and water; gradually stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta noodles.
Add rest of ingredients. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and garnish with your favorite Italian dressing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind or chop first 5 ingredients in food processor.
In a large bowl, mix jello, water and sugar well, then add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add everything except sour cream.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add sour cream.
Serve over chips; top with lettuce, tomatoes, grated cheese, green onions, black olives, etc.

title: cassoulet, french casserole
directions: Split sausage in half lengthwise and pan-fry until brown.
Cut into 2 or 3 pieces each.
Defrost lima beans until separated and mix with other beans.
Mix sausage, ham and beans.
Combine seasoning, tomato sauce, ketchup, brown sugar and onion.
Add to meat and bean mixture.
Pour all into crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then turn on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: fat man cakes
directions: Cream brown sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until dough plops in the middle.
Cut in squares while hot and roll in powdered sugar.

title: greek cabbage salad
directions: Place the cabbage, Feta and dill in a large bowl.
Put the oil, lemon juice, Parmesan, mustard and oregano in a small bowl or jar and stir or shake until combined.
Pour the dressing over the salad and toss until well mixed.

title: corn for freezing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes, stirring often to keep from sticking to pot.
Drain any remaining water.
Cool and freeze.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat with onions and drain. Stir in all but Worcestershire sauce and cheese. Cook 20 minutes at 400°. Then add cheese and Worcestershire sauce on top and cook for 10 more minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before eating. Serves 4 to 6.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef with 1 onion; drain.
Add beans, canned tomatoes, taco sauce and mix in garlic, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Top chips with meat sauce, olives, fresh tomato, lettuce, onion and sour cream.

title: pineapple sheet cake(hawaiian wedding cake)
directions: Mix together and bake in a greased and floured 10 x 14-inch sheet cake pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Overnight is best, but can be for just a few hours, if necessary.
Serve with fresh, cut up vegetables (carrots, celery, radishes, zucchini, cauliflower and broccoli).

title: ice cream custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Cover and continue cooking for 10 minutes.
Stir a small amount of the hot milk into the beaten eggs, then stir into the remaining hot milk. Cook over hot, not boiling water, until mixture coats the spoon. Remove from hot water and chill.
Add vanilla and cream, then your fruit or whatever flavor desired.

title: low-fat healthy chili in crock-pot
directions: Trim the veal of all visible fat. Cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Place meat in crock-pot and stir in tomato sauce to completely coat meat. Add remaining ingredients and stir to blend. Do not add any additional liquid. Cover and cook for 12 hours on low heat. When done, skim fat from surface and discard. Serve this low-fat dish with rice, beans or crackers.

title: bunny muffins(these muffins are so good and healthy, too!)
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Fill greased (use Pam and sprinkle with sugar) muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until golden brown. Enjoy!

title: sourdough bread
directions: Keep starter in refrigerator with top off.
Starter can be used every 3 to 5 days.
To use starter, feed starter with 1/4 cup instant potatoes, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 cup warm water.
Let stand, morning until night, at room temperature.
Then use 1 cup of this starter; put rest back in refrigerator.
Then add 1/2 cup corn oil, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 1/2 cups warm water and 6 cups bread flour (not sifted).
After mixing, grease large bowl.
Put dough in and turn several times so dough is covered with oil.
Let stand several (8 to 10) hours.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor.
Stir in pineapple and sugar; set aside for 15 minutes.
Fold cranberry mixture into Cool Whip, then fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice.
Dice onions and dice the celery.
Put oil in large frying pan.
Beat egg and add to oil, cutting into strips.
Add garlic powder, salt and soy sauce.
Mix well and add cooked rice, stirring until browned by the soy sauce.
Add diced celery and diced onions to the rice.

title: homemade snicker bars
directions: Melt 1/2 the chips and 1/2 Crisco in microwave until smooth. Add 1/2 peanuts to melted chocolate, spread nutty chocolate in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate while melting caramels, oleo and water in microwave until smooth.
Add remaining peanuts to caramel and spread over first chocolate layer.
Refrigerate while melting 1/2 the chips and 1/2 Crisco.
Spread over caramel layer. Chill until firm.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Bake squash until done, then remove seeds and scrape out pulp. Put in blender with other ingredients until all is mixed well. Pour into greased 4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch casserole dish (loaf pan). Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until casserole is set.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients together until creamy and smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and
cook
for
minutes
at 325° to 350°. Time of preparation: 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: kielbasi snacks
directions: Slice kielbasi and fry slightly to get the grease out.
Mix preserves, ginger, lemon juice and mustard.
Add kielbasi; microwave or put in crock-pot and heat.
Serve warm.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Cut in butter with 2 knives or pastry blender.
Add buttermilk and mix quickly but thoroughly.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead lightly for a few seconds.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness and cut. Place on buttered baking sheet and brush with milk.
Bake in very hot oven.

title: summer cooler
directions: Dissolve gelatin in
boiling
water.
Stir in fruit and corn syrup.
Beat in
egg
using
wire
whisk.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours.
Spoon half the mixture into blender
or
food processor.
Blend at high speed until smooth, but
not
melted, about 30 seconds.
Repeat with other half.
Pour into 9	x
5-inch
loaf
pan
or 1 1/2 quart container.	cover;	freeze	until
firm, 6 hours or overnight. Makes 6 servings.

title: oatmeal cake with icing
directions: Soak oats in water for 20 minutes.
Cream butter and sugars. Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed mixture.
Bake in 12 x 9 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prune bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients, alternating to egg mixture with 1 cup buttermilk. Add vanilla.
Fold in prunes and nuts.

title: hanky panky
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger and drain.
Add Velveeta and spices.
Melt cheese.
Spread on party rye.
Put on broiler pan and broil in oven until it bubbles and browns slightly.
These can be frozen on the cookie sheet and then stored in plastic bags until ready to use at a later date.
Reheat frozen under broiler for about 5 to 6 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In 13 1/2 x 10 x 3-inch pan spread crushed pineapple.
Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherry pie filling, breaking lumps with fork.
Slice sticks of oleo or butter over cake mix, being sure that cake mix is covered. Sprinkle nuts over top. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown. Top with whipped topping if desired.

title: monkey face cookies
directions: Put raisins in hot water, then add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm.

title: homemade mustard
directions: Blend mustard, vinegar and eggs in blender.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Combine beef, wine, consomme, onion, salt, pepper and mushrooms in casserole.
Mix sifted flour and bread crumbs.
Stir into beef mixture.
Cover casserole tightly.
Bake for three hours or until done at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Very easy and tasty!
French.

title: corned beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni.
Add butter, salt, cheese, beef and onion.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cake mix oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine oil and eggs. Add dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Do not use mixer.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Shape into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten balls with slightly greased glass bottom or fork.
Bake 12 minutes, until lightly browned.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cheese, sugar, milk and peanut butter.
Fold whipped topping into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate and chill.
Top with peanuts.

title: santa fe stew
directions: Cook meat and onions until meat loses its pink color.
Add beans, corn, tomatoes and seasonings.
Mix well and simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Serve with cornbread, rice or crackers. Freezes well.

title: aunt bill's brown candy
directions: Pour 1 pint sugar into heavy aluminum or iron skillet and place over low heat.
Begin stirring with wooden spoon and keep sugar moving so it will not scorch at all.
It will take over 1/2 an hour to completely melt this sugar and at no time let it smoke or cook so fast that it turns dark.
It should be about the color of light brown sugar syrup.

As soon as you have the sugar started to heat in skillet, pour the remaining 2 pints of sugar together with pint of milk into deep, heavy kettle and set it over low heat to cook along slowly while melting sugar in skillet.

title: pancho pie
directions: Combine chopped pepper, garlic and shortening in frying pan. Add beef, chili powder and salt.
Boil briskly, then stir in corn meal, milk, mixed olives and mushrooms.
Pour into casserole and bake at 325° for about 1 hour until set.
Top with grated cheese before baking if desired.

title: poncho's baked beans
directions: Prepare lima beans according to package directions; drain. Brown ground round.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Drain carrots.
Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots. Put in oven about 30 minutes at 350°, until bubbly.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix well and place in nonmetallic bowl for 48 hours. Refrigerate.
Add when using 1 1/2 cups flour and water.

title: crabby mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss crabmeat with lemon juice.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Fill mushroom caps and sprinkle with cheese.
Rinse baking sheet with water and arrange mushroom caps on sheet.
Cover with foil and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 5 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 5 minutes or until golden.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut in an electric blender. Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pan. Let stand for 5 minutes; sprinkle with coconut (and cinnamon and nutmeg, if desired).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandpa's rolls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in water and add to mixture.
Add salt and flour.
Mix well.
Cover bowl and let set until dough is about double in size (takes about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Put out on floured surface and knead for about 2 minutes.
Let set again until double in size (1 1/2 to 2 hours). Roll into small balls about the size of a walnut.
Put 3 of these in each cup of greased cupcake pan.
Let rise again until about double in size.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: maple or vanilla pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients except flavoring and pecans; cook slowly to 234°.
Add flavoring.
Remove from heat; cool.
Beat and add chopped pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Yield: Approximately 30 pieces.

title: low-fat pudding pie
directions: Mix chocolate pudding with 2 cups milk according to directions, then put into pie shell.
Mix pistachio pudding according to directions and put on top of chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: strawberry bavarian
directions: Prepare Jell-O as package directs.
After Jell-O is set, whip it with electric mixer.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Fold in strawberries and refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Cream together margarine, oil, eggs, vanilla and sour cream. Sift together flour, cocoa, spices, baking powder and baking soda. Gradually add to first mixture.
Fold in zucchini.
Pour into greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top; stir into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix all except brown sugar and cinnamon.
Beat 3 minutes. Pour half of the mixture into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter in pan. Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: susan's chicken wings
directions: Wash and dry winglets (discarding tips).
Salt and pepper to taste, then bake at 375° in a ceramic or glass dish, covered with foil for 45 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over wings.
Bake, uncovered, 50 minutes at 400°, stirring once or twice, if desired.

title: ice cream squares
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter; place in 8 x 8-inch pan. Dissolve jello n boiling water; add ice cream and blend well. Pour over bottom layer and refrigerate.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, rice, soup and 1/2 cup onion in 2-quart casserole pan.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes. Microwave cheese spread according to label.
Stir cheese spread into broccoli mixture.
Top with remaining onion. Microwave 2 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix ingredients and add flour to make a stiff dough.
Let rise once and roll out dough like you were making dumplings.
Cut in small strips and dip each piece in melted margarine and layer in Bundt pan.
Fill about half full, let rise again and bake in moderate oven until done.
Serve warm.

title: baked chicken breasts #1
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with dried onion flakes.
Fold over breasts.
Put into baking dish.
Cover with soup, diluted with sherry.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook at least 45 minutes longer or until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill well. Serve with bread or crackers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Chill.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Mix ingredients in Ziploc.
Add pork tenderloins.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours at room temperature.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° uncovered. Put a little marinade in dish while cooking.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown pork in skillet.
Remove linguica from casing; chop and add to pork.
Drain and add 2 tablespoons soy sauce and garlic powder.
Mix well.

title: trifle
directions: In a medium bowl, fold sour cream and pudding mix into the whipped topping.
Cut the cake into thirds, horizontally.

Line a large trifle or other glass serving bowl with kiwi and strawberry slices, reserving two whole strawberries and two kiwi slices. Place one layer of cake on bottom of bowl, top with 1/3 bananas and pineapple, and 1/3 whipped topping mixture.
Repeat layering until all ingredients are used.
Make fan garnishes of whole strawberries by slicing from just below the stem.
Garnish assembled trifle with fanned strawberries, reserved kiwi slices, and the sprig of mint. Refrigerate until serving.

title: bread and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use sliced whole wheat or any kind of leftover bread, stale is okay too!
Toast and cut into smaller pieces.
In casserole dish, put layer of bread, layer of cheese and layer of vegetables.
Salt and pepper.
Dot with butter or sprinkle with oil (no olive oil).
Repeat until everything is used up.
Heat milk and beat in eggs.
Pour over whole thing.
Bake for 40 minutes or until milk is absorbed and cheese is melted and bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: nibblin' fish snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except for oil.
Stir together until thoroughly combined.
Drizzle with oil and mix until coated.
Transfer to sealable, airtight container.
Stores up to 1 week.
Makes about 12 cups mix.

title: hot fudge ice cream cake
directions: Mix together cookies and 1 stick melted butter.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze.
Spread ice cream on top and freeze.
Bring to a boil in pan the sugar, milk, chocolate and butter.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Cool 15 minutes.
Spread on ice cream and freeze.

title: aunt mildred's apple cake
directions: In a large bowl put in the oil.
Gradually add the sugar, beating until well creamed.
Add the eggs, one at a time and mix well. Add vanilla.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat an iron skillet with approximately 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Pour mixture into heated skillet. Bake at 500° until brown.

title: three bean salad
directions: In large bowl, combine green beans, wax beans, kidney beans and green pepper; mix well.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over beans and toss gently.
Chill overnight. Toss again before serving.

title: pineapple silver
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in lukewarm milk and set aside.
Sift flour and then measure.
Add butter or oleo; mix like for pie crust.
Add yeast and milk mixture to beaten egg yolks; mix well.

title: ginger creams
directions: Add to melted shortening and mix well.
Spread on large cookie sheet with edges.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost while warm with thin confectioners sugar icing.
(Dough can also be dropped by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet 2 1/2 inches apart.)

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix and knead as for pie dough.
Roll in balls the size of a marble.
Place ball in sugar.
Press into candy mold or press flat with fork, crisscross fashion.

title: creole hamburger
directions: Fry hamburger in patties as for regular hamburgers and drain. Combine cans of soup (add 3/4 can of water to each can of soup), onions, celery and green pepper.
Cook until onions, celery and green peppers are tender.
Crumble patties and add to soup mixture. Simmer on low until the mixture becomes thick.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve on slightly toasted open hamburger buns.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium size saucepan, heat butter or margarine over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat. With whisk, beat in syrup, sugar, eggs and vanilla until blended.
Put nuts in bottom of pie shell.
Carefully pour liquid over nuts. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near edge comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: marble brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on box (use "cake-like" directions).
Set aside.

title: ham sandwich spread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on desired breads.

title: cheesy egg souffle
directions: 1. Beat the eggs briskly.
Dissolve cornstarch in the milk and mix into the eggs along with the remaining ingred ients. 2. Pour into a well greased souffle pan.
Cook in a 300° oven until a well tanned formed dome forms.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and mayonnaise in large bowl; beat at medium mixer speed until smooth.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon in foil lined loaf pan.
Freeze 8 hours.
Remove 10 minutes before serving and cut into slices.
Makes 10 servings.

title: amish carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut carrots into strips and steam them for about 8 minutes.
Mix mayo, horseradish and water.
Turn carrots into a baking dish; pour in mayo mixture and mix to coat evenly.
Season lightly with pepper and sprinkle almonds over top. Bake for about 10 minutes and serve immediately.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in double boiler or over low heat.
Sift cocoa and powdered sugar (no lumps).
Mix sugar/cocoa mixture into melted mixture and blend thoroughly (use your hands).
Add nuts and vanilla; blend again.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pans.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
7 pounds.
Freezes well.

title: senator salad
directions: Put all the vegetables into a large bowl.
Place vinegar, sugar and oil in pan and simmer until it reaches the boiling point.
Stir and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: microwave chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken and paprika, in a 13 x 9-inch microwave-safe dish.
Arrange chicken on top, meaty side up, in a single layer.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 25 to 30 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn twice until chicken is barely opaque in thickest part when tested with a knife.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes, until opaque.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mary's crispy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy. Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Drop with teaspoon and press with fork. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Beat egg and stir in buttermilk and oil.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together; add to liquid ingredients, beating until smooth.
Pour lemon juice over grated apple and stir into batter.
Bake on a lightly greased hot griddle, turning when pancakes are puffed and full of bubbles.
Serve together with alternate layers of hot applesauce and brown sugar.
Sprinkle the top with brown sugar.
Makes 16 pancakes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Layer the herbs and eggs in a glass jar with a tight fitting lid.
Cover with the vinegar and seal.
Let stand in a cool, dark place for 1 week before using.
The eggs will then keep in the refrigerator for about 2 months.
After the eggs are eaten, the vinegar can be used in salads or marinades.
For variation, you can add a sliced lemon or a sliced onion.

title: fluffy rice and chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup and milk.
Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Mix remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms with liquid and 1/2 of onion soup mix; pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put cut up chicken on top.
Pour on remaining soup mix. Sprinkle rest of onion soup mix on top.
Bake for 1 hour, covered with foil.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pizza style macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in frying pan.
In a 10-inch casserole dish, combine cooked macaroni and beef mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce, water and seasoning. Toss.
Sprinkle top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and toppings.
Pour the rest of the sauce and spread.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shanghai chicken wings
directions: Cut wings to make 2 pieces.
Combine soy sauce, syrup, catsup, sherry, ginger and garlic.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour sauce over; coat well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Bake at 375° in sauce, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use extra sauce for dipping.

title: oatmeal date cookies
directions: Cream butter. Add sugars and cream well. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour. Add soda, baking powder and cinnamon to flour. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Add oatmeal, dates, nuts and coconut. Let stand 15 minutes. Bake at 325° for approximately 12 minutes on a greased or aluminum foil covered cookie sheet. Cookies mellow as they are stored.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, milk, curry, salt, soy sauce and lemon juice.

title: jollof rice
directions: Salt and pepper chicken, then brown in oil.
Then fry onions and 1 or 2 hot peppers.
Boil together chicken, bouillon cubes, tomato paste, onions, vegetables and rice (salt according to taste).
After bringing to a boil, turn heat low for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover, stirring occasionally.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Drain and pour corn and green beans in a 2-quart baking dish. Combine pepper, soup, onion, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over corn and beans.
Mix well.
Before putting in the oven, pour melted oleo over and sprinkle with crackers and almonds.
Bake at 300°
for 45 minutes.

title: brown and serve pizza
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add hot water and oil; mix.
Add enough extra flour to make dough stiff. Knead about 5 minutes.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Divide in half.
Roll each into crust.
Place on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When cool, wrap and store in refrigerator for up to 1 week.
Or cover with tomato sauce and your favorite pizza toppings.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Spread pineapple over pan. Spread cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and/or coconut over cake mix. Do not mix.
Cut margarine into chunks and cover mixture with it. Bake 55 minutes at 350°.
If top is not crispy, turn oven up to 400° and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Watch carefully as it can burn easily.
Cool and serve.

title: mary ellen's supper rolls
directions: Put water and yeast together and mix well.
Add oil, sugar and salt and mix well.
Add 1 3/4 cups flour and stir in.
Add extra flour and work up good.
Pinch off by hand and shape into rolls. Put cooking oil in Corning Ware pan and grease sides of rolls. Let rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix and place in a greased pan.
Put chopped nuts on top. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lasagna microwave
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, the egg and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Spread 1/3 of sauce in bottom of 12 x 18-inch baking dish. Arrange 3 noodles on top.
Spread with half the Ricotta mixture. Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers once.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Top with sauce.
Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 8 minutes. Rotate dish.
Reduce to Medium-low for 30 to 35 minutes longer or until noodles are tender, rotating dish once.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Re-cover.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 3-quart oblong baking dish.

title: can can chicken
directions: In large bowl, combine soup and milk.
Mix well.
Add chestnuts, mushrooms, noodles, chicken, pimiento and peas; stir until mixed.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: phyllis snyder's walnut cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Fold in nuts and egg whites.
Grease two 8-inch layer pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with any white frosting; sprinkle with 1/4 cup chopped walnuts.

title: everyday coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with topping.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour angel food pan.
Mix margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and continue to beat after each addition.
This mixture will become very fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately until all is used, making the dry ingredients last. Add vanilla and continue to beat for at least 10 minutes.
Turn batter into pan and bake in oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cool on wire rack.
May frost, if desired.
Buttercream icing is a great icing for this cake.
Stores well.
Serves 20.

title: potluck spaghetti
directions: I use small oval roaster for boiling spaghetti.
In boiling water, cook onion and celery until tender.
Add the spaghetti. Cook according to directions or boil a few minutes, stir often, turn off heat and cover.
Steam will continue the cooking.

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: *May omit salt and add other spices.

title: frank and potato bake
directions: Reserve 3 franks; slice remaining franks and set aside. In saucepan,
stir milk into flour until smooth.
Add cheese; cook and stir until thickened and smooth.
Add onion, parsley and
1/2 teaspoon salt.
Fold cheese mixture into potatoes and sliced franks.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at
350° for
minutes.
Halve reserved franks; arrange in pinwheel
on top casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Top with parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain oysters.
Saute oysters in 3 tablespoons butter until edges curl.
Add butter, milk, juice, garlic and Tony Chachere seasoning (to taste).
Bring to a simmer.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients thoroughly; pour into casserole. Add raisins and/or coconut.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sugar and cinnamon. Pour liquid over bread in pudding dish. Let stand till soaked. Add raisins. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Should be firm.

title: old-fashioned apple pies
directions: Pare and core apples; cut in quarters and slice thin.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Mix sugar, flour and spices.
Rub a little sugar mixture into pastry.
Arrange sliced apples, overlapping in pan.
Dot with butter.
Cut slits in top crust. Moisten edges of lower crust and place top crust over apples; press edges together, trim and flute edges.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white, if desired, or sprinkle lightly with sugar. Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: transparent pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks that have been well beaten.
Add flavoring.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake slowly until firm.

title: cornbread-sausage stuffing with apples
directions: Saute chopped onions in 1 cup apple cider; cook partially covered until tender and lightly colored, about 25 minutes. Transfer onions and cider to large mixing bowl.
Cook apple chunks in 1 cup apple cider on high heat, stirring until lightly colored but not mushy.
Transfer apples and 1/2 of the juice to the mixing bowl.
Crumble ground turkey into the skillet with the other 1/2 of the apple juice.
Stir in 2 teaspoons of sage and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until done.
Add remaining ingredients to the ingredients in the mixing bowl and combine gently.
Cool completely before stuffing the bird; refrigerate if not used promptly.

title: angel coffee almond cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Bake according to package directions.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw frozen bread dough or use pizza dough.
Roll out in a rectangle shape as a jelly roll.
Place on dough in the following order:
Provolone cheese, boiled ham, pepperoni, salami, green pepper, onion, mushrooms and pizza sauce.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with hash brown potatoes.
Melt margarine in small pot and pour 1/2 of the margarine over potatoes and set rest of the side.
Melt Cheez Whiz and then combine Cheez Whiz and cream of chicken soup together. Pour them over the potatoes.
Pour the 1/2 margarine that you have set aside over the crushed cornflakes and then pour this over the potatoes, Cheez Whiz and cream of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: triple-treat brownie crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Chop unsweetened chocolate.
Combine 6 tablespoons butter and half the chopped chocolate in pan over lowest heat.
Let melt and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool.
Butter a 9-inch cake pan.
With electric mixer, beat eggs until frothy; still beating, gradually add sugar.
Beat until thick and pale yellow.
Turn to low and beat in 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla and the salt.
Beat in the melted chocolate and butter mixture. With a spoon, stir in flour.
Pour into pan and bake until done in center, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert onto rack and cool.
Chop candy bar.
Combine remaining 3 ounces chocolate with remaining 3 tablespoons of butter in a saucepan over lowest heat.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Combine ingredients in order given except soup and water.
Mold into loaf on 8 x 10-inch greased roaster or pan (2 smaller loaves may be made).
Place in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes (your oven temperature may differ).
Combine soup and boiling water. Pour over meat loaf.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Garnish with parsley.
Serve the sauce as gravy.
If preferred some spicy canned tomatoes may be used.
(After meat loaves are made, one may be frozen and baked at a later date.)

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cook slowly 4 or 5 hours.

title: punch
directions: Make jello according to package directions. Add other ingredients.
Freeze.
Take from freezer in time to thaw to icy slush to serve.
Can use any flavor jello and Hi-C.

title: ostakaka
directions: Heat milk until it is lukewarm.
Crush rennet tablet and beat eggs slightly.
Add flour, eggs and rennet to lukewarm milk.
Stir well and let stand one hour.
Do not touch during this time.
After cheese has set, drain off the whey from the curd.
(Note:
Take 1/2 or more whey.)
Cut up cheese just enough to break it up into small pieces.
Put cheese in a greased casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Then pour the cream, sugar and almond flavoring over it and bake 45 minutes more.

title: summer chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate in 2 tablespoons milk over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Beat remaining milk, cream cheese and sugar together.
Add to chocolate; beat.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Remove about 20 minutes before serving.
Garnish with Cool Whip and shaved chocolate.

title: mom's peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Mix
all
ingredients, adding flour slowly.
Roll in small balls and place on cookie sheet. Press down with fork.	Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mother's caramel filling and frosting
directions: Put 3 cups sugar and milk into heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil.

In heavy skillet (mother used a cast-iron skillet), add 1 cup sugar. Cook until caramelized, stirring constantly. Add hot syrup to caramelized mixture, stirring constantly. Add butter and cook until reaches soft ball stage (about 240°).
Remove from heat and beat until creamy.
Yield:
Covers two 9-inch layers.

title: yam yums
directions: Toss apples and nuts with sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate apples and yams in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and broil until lightly browned.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes. When cake is cool, ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Place milk, butter and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Syrup should form a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat and fold in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Add nuts, if desired. Pour in greased pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: eggless tofu mayonnaise
directions: In blender jar, put tofu with mustard and 1/2 tablespoon lemon juice.
Blend until combined.
Drop by drop, slowly blend in oil. Stop blender and scrape sides of blender jar.
Add drops of lemon juice alternately with the oil until used up.
The slower you combine ingredients, the thicker the mayonnaise will be.
Season carefully to taste with salt and white pepper.
For better flavor, cover and chill mayonnaise for at least 24 hours before using. Mayonnaise will keep covered in refrigerator for at least two weeks.
Yield:
about 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into greased baking dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Melt margarine; mix with potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, onions, cream of chicken soup, cheese and sour cream.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
