Top with flakes and margarine.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: creamy double decker fudge
directions: Combine peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup milk.
Cook in microwave on 100% power, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute, until chips are melted.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Spread in 8-inch pan.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple; stir until pineapple is coated.
Combine butter and crackers; spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lettuce layer salad
directions: Wash and tear lettuce; dry and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Fry bacon and crumble.
Boil and chop eggs.
Sprinkle egg, bacon, green pepper and onion over lettuce.
Cover with salad dressing (Miracle Whip).
End with shredded cheese.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain and thaw spinach.
Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate overnight.
This is very good served in round bread (ordered from grocery store), hollowed out.
Cube bread taken out of middle and put around outside of round bread with spinach dip in it.

title: sausage-rye appetizers
directions: Combine sausage and ground beef.
Brown and drain; add Velveeta to mixture and stir until melted.
Add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce and mix.
Spread mixture on rye bread. Arrange on foil tray.
You may freeze at this point, if desired, or bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: it's a cookie!
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll dough into balls, use 1 teaspoon of dough for each ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 1-inch apart.
Press with bottom of glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
Easy and great for kids.

title: gelatin cream cheese
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar in large bowl.
Soften gelatin in boiling water and add to cream cheese mixture.
Add lemon juice, milk and vanilla to gelatin/cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Grease mold with mayonnaise.
Pour mixture into mold; cool until set.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients except tomato soup.
Form into balls.
Put into small roaster.
Pour tomato soup over meat balls.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes.

title: low-fat "not fried rice"
directions: Coat medium saucepan with Pam cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and saute in liquid Butter Buds or chicken broth for 2 minutes.
Add 2 cups chicken broth and next 3 ingredients; bring to boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat and stir in green onions and pine nuts.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Grease pie plate.
Sprinkle with flour.
Combine sugar, flour, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Blend well together.
Add milk and blend until smooth.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir together and serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburg, onions and green peppers.
Add uncooked rice or noodles, tomatoes and seasonings.
Put in crock-pot and let set for as long as you want.

title: hot butter sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Brown slightly. Add sugar and cream, mixing well.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately or reheat to serve later.
Yield: Sauce for 8 to 9-inch square cake.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Cut in Crisco.
Add enough milk to make stiff dough.
Turn onto floured board; knead.
Roll into rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Roll in jelly roll; cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Bake at 475° for 20 minutes.
Dribble with thin powdered sugar frosting.
Serves 12.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Place oregano and Shake 'N Bake in bag.
Mix.
Prepare chicken and bake according to directions on package.
When chicken is done, sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes longer until cheese is melted.
Do not spoon drippings over chicken.

title: steak marinade
directions: Combine soy sauce, onions and garlic in electric blender. Blend for 1 minute on high or until mixture is very smooth.
Stir in Gravy Master and salt.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.
Pour over meat and allow to stand at room temperature for 2 1/2 hours or cover dish with plastic wrap and keep in refrigerator for up to 24 hours.
Bring meat to room temperature before cooking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients together and place over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: italian sausage strata
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
Brown sausage in skillet about 10 minutes, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as it browns.
Stir in green pepper and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, breaking up pieces.
Cook 15 minutes to remove most of the liquid.

title: "penne pasta with artichokes and sun dried tomatoes"
directions: Saute garlic in oil in a large saute pan until it becomes light gold in color. Add mushrooms and sun dried tomatoes.
Saute until mushrooms become tender.
Add diced tomatoes, parsley, basil, sherry and Chablis and cook uncovered until
liquid is reduced by half.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Trim off excess fat.
Brown roast.
Combine ingredients and pour over meat.
Cook until tender.
Shred beef and return to oven or slow cooker until desired consistency.

title: zesty burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Broil or grill about 8 to 10 minutes, turning once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: humble pie
directions: Slice pound cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook pudding as directed on box.
Cool, slice bananas over cake and pour pudding over bananas.
Place in refrigerator until cold.
Make meringue with egg whites, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over pudding, sprinkle with coconut.
Bake until browned.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Prepare muffin mix, using package directions.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into nonstick baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal fudge drops
directions: Mix together the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: heavenly cream pie
directions: Melt margarine; add cup of flour, 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Mix together and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown. Cool crust.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix vanilla pudding according to directions on box.
Pour over first layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on vanilla pudding.
Top Cool Whip with coconut and pecans on top of coconut.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add 1 cup sugar and beat well.
Add condensed milk, evaporated milk and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into freezer can of a 5-quart hand-turned or electric freezer; add milk.
Turn about 5 minutes or until custard is thick.
Combine peaches and remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Remove dasher and add peaches to cream mixture.
Return dasher to freezer and continue turning until ready.
Let ice cream ripen about 1 hour.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans on buttered bottom. Place frozen rolls on top of pecans.
Sprinkle pudding over rolls. In a saucepan, melt margarine and brown sugar; drizzle over rolls.
Cover with waxed paper sprayed with Pam.
Leave out overnight (or at least 6 hours).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
(Place on cookie sheet in oven to prevent sugar from boiling over into oven.)
Let set a couple of minutes, loosen edges and flip onto cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Let stand overnight in 2 quarts of water and salt.
Next day, rinse and drain well.
Bring to a boil.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery and turmeric to cucumbers.
Heat just until tender.
Place in canning jars.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Put 1/2 stuffing in bottom of dish.
Mix all ingredients except squash together, then stir in squash and pour over stuffing mix.
Dot with butter and cover with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: clam cocktail dunk
directions: Drain clams.
Stir cream cheese to soften.
Add remaining ingredients
and beat with electric or rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Stir in clams.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: nutty chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix together all of the ingredients except Chinese noodles.
Put into an ungreased casserole dish. Sprinkle Chinese noodles on top and bake for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop supper
directions: Trim fat from chops; cook trimmings in skillet until 2 tablespoons accumulate.
Discard trimmings.
Brown chops slowly in hot drippings; set aside chops.
Reserve drippings.
In same skillet, cook rice and onion in droppings until rice is golden, stirring constantly.
Stir in water and bouillon.
Bring to boil. Stir in chopped apple.
Turn into baking dish.
Arrange chops on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no fault pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll out dough and place in pie pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Never fails!

title: filled pockets
directions: Cut butter and cheese into flour.
Roll about 1/8-inch thick; cut circles.
Put 1 teaspoon filling; fold over and crimp.
Bake on cookie sheet, ungreased, at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (not brown).

title: hot spiced apricot tea
directions: Combine
cloves
and
cinnamon
in
cheesecloth and set aside. Bring
water to boil in large saucepan.
Add tea bags. Remove from heat and steep 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add spice mixture
(in
cheesecloth) and remaining ingredients to tea; bring
to
boil.
Remove
spices
and serve hot.
Yield: about 6 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add first mixture to the flour mixture; mix well, then add pecans and vanilla.
Bake for 25 minutes at 300°.
Cover top of cake with miniature marshmallows and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Let cool and cover with icing.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook fryer in several cups of water until tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Let cool and remove skin.
Remove chicken from bones.
In a large mixing bowl, place flour.
Into this nest, add salt, shortening, chicken broth and cold water.
Mix with hands until dough is firm enough to roll.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rice in a lightly greased baking dish.
Rinse and pat dry chicken pieces.
Arrange chicken over rice.

title: aunt emily's beef stew
directions: Coat beef cubes with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Boil together all other ingredients except vegetables and sherry.
Add vegetables.
Add sherry and cook for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Remove stems and wash strawberries. Drain thoroughly on paper towels. Place berries in pie shell, arranging carefully, placing biggest on top. Combine sugar, cornstarch, gelatin and water in saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and clear. Add several drops of food coloring to make a rich red color. Cool 15 minutes.
Pour over berries, making sure to cover all berries. Refrigerate. Serve with whipped cream. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: strawberry bread
directions: You will also need a mixing bowl and 2 loaf pans.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain sweet potatoes; mash well and measure 3 cups. Melt 1/2 stick of margarine. Beat eggs well. Add together sweet potatoes, margarine, eggs, sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and cinnamon. Mix well and put in 2-quart baking dish.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in saucepan.
Add broth.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour into ovenproof soup bowls.
Add approximately 10 croutons to each bowl.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is slightly browned and bubbly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 2.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Make pudding according to directions.

Fold in whipped topping. In a 9 x 13 inch pan, layer whipped mixture and then a layer of graham crackers. Repeat four layers, ending with graham crackers on top. Remove foil from can of frosting and replace lid.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Pour frosting over the top of graham crackers and spread evenly.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: brandied peach marmalade
directions: Skin and pit peaches.
Chop.
Remove peel, white portion and seeds from oranges.
Chop.
Put all ingredients except brandy into a large kettle.
Boil on medium-high heat, stirring frequently to prevent scorching until mixture thickens, about 45 minutes.
Stir in brandy.
Ladle into jars and seal.

title: pasta shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and toss with French dressing.
Chill 1 hour.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Serve on lettuce.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss together; serve cold.

title: sunday brunch bake
directions: Butter 2-quart baking dish.
Layer bread cubes, ham and grated cheese.
Mix flour and mustard; sprinkle over cheese.
Drizzle butter over all.
Beat eggs and milk together and add Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over layers.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve immediately.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown beef with garlic; drain off fat.
Mix next 4 ingredients and stir into beef.
Stuff shells.
Arrange in greased Pyrex pan. Pour sauce over shells and sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered with aluminum foil. Remove foil after 15 minutes and bake 10 more minutes.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon, together lightly with fork. Shape into 4 round steaks.
Wrap each steak with a slice of bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Broil 6-inches from heat for 8 to 11 minutes.
Remove toothpicks before serving.

title: honey lemon sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.
Use to baste chicken.

title: cheese stuffed strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients except berries and mint in blender or food processor until fluffy.
Refrigerate and chill for 1 hour.
Scoop out centers of berries.
Fill with cheese mixture.
Garnish each berry with mint sprig.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook carrots and broccoli tender-crisp.
Add chopped onion and green pepper. Cover with some of the Italian dressing.
Combine cooled vegetables with cooled rotini, Parmesan cheese and remaining dressing.
Layer in bowl with shredded cheese and sliced olives. Better after the first day.
Makes lots.

title: luncheon fruit salad
directions: Heat pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Do not boil; soften gelatin with a little cold water and add a little of the warm pineapple mixture to it.
Mix well so it won't lump.
Mash cheese; add to preceding; also add cherries, cut up in pieces, with enough maraschino juice to make a pink color.
Let set until quite thick, then add whipped cream.
Put in a mold or just in a dish.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, onion, cheese and garlic powder until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix margarine and 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder (depending on taste).
Brush over warm biscuits.

title: chocolate flavored syrup
directions: Mix cocoa, water and salt in a heavy saucepan until smooth. Bring to a boil and simmer gently, stirring constantly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; let cool 10 minutes.
Add sweetener and vanilla and mix well. Pour into jar, cover and store in refrigerator.
Stir in jar before measuring to use. Yields 20 servings, 1 1/2 cups, 1 serving tablespoon.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Measure in bowl; add salt and cut in Crisco until fine.
Add ice water and mix dough.
It should be firm enough to roll.
Roll thin as possible and cut.
Drop in boiling broth.
Cook over medium heat.
Cook 10 minutes with lid on and 10 more with lid off.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops slowly; add salt and pepper.
Scrape tomato paste all out into about 2-quart bowl; add water until you have plenty to cover well as they have to bake in the oven 35 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with about 3 tablespoons leaf oregano over the top before you put in oven.

title: tempting tuna melt
directions: Heat broiler.
Mix tuna, dressing, onions, red pepper and seasonings.
For each sandwich, top English muffin half with lettuce, tomato and tuna mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Broil 1 minute.
Top with slice of cheese.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.
Makes 4 servings.

title: otherma's jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until very thick. Add water. Add sifted dry ingredients by folding in gently. Line a cookie sheet with greased wax paper. Pour in batter and spread evenly. Bake about 12 minutes at 375° to 400°. Turn out onto a cloth sprinkled with powdered sugar. Cut off crisp edge of cake; slowly tear off wax paper, then spread with warmed jelly or jam. Roll up quickly with the seam to the bottom. Let cool before slicing.

title: sausage and peppers "sauce"
directions: Place crushed tomatoes and Del Monte sauce in a pot and simmer. Dice onion and add to pot.
Clean and fry peppers.
After frying, place in pot.
After browning sausage well, then add to pot.
Mix chopped meat, 1 egg and bread crumbs together.
Roll into meatballs; brown well and add to pot.
Cover the pot and cook on low heat for about 3 hours.
When finished cooking, place on your favorite pasta or eat alone.
Enjoy!

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Roll hot dog and 1 slice cheese in 1 crescent roll.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mock champagne
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Cool.
Add grapefruit, orange juice and ginger ale.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt-set aside.
Mash the bananas with the vanilla-let sit 10 minutes.
Add to the bananas the sugar and eggs-beat well.
Stir in melted butter and flour mixture just until blended.
Turn into greased 8x4 inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350°F. for 1 hour or until pick inserted in center comes out moist but clean.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add fruit cocktail.
Mix and pour in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cover with topping.

title: stewed chicken and dumplings
directions: Clean chicken; rub skin with baking soda and wash off carefully.
Cut up chicken; peel off excess fat.
Fit chicken pieces completely in cooking kettle.
Add salt; cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and stir until mixture is dampened.
Add parsley; stir until distributed evenly.
Add to chicken.
Cook until done.
Remove chicken to platter and dumplings to gravy bowl.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter until transparent.
Add garlic cheese until melted.
Add broccoli (cooked per package directions), mushroom soup and mushroom pieces.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Place into fondue.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: macaroons ii
directions: Cut almond paste into very small pieces in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and the egg whites.
Blend until very smooth.
Pipe cookies or by the teaspoon, about the size of half a dollar onto a brown paper lined baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes. Allow to cool.
Dampen the back of the brown paper and remove cookies.

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter in bowl.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour; stir until smooth.
Shape dough in ball.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill 1 hour.
Saute mushrooms and onion in 1 1/2 tablespoons butter in heavy skillet over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, salt, thyme and 1 tablespoon flour. Roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with 4-inch circle.
Place 1/2 teaspoon mushroom mixture in center of each.
Fold dough in half and press edges with fingers.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush tops with egg and prick top with fork.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Freezes well.
This is worth the effort!

title: marinade for beef to barbecue
directions: Sprinkle roast with tenderizer on both sides.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Let stand in refrigerator for 6 hours, turning once after 3 hours.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil; add lime jello.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese.
Refrigerate until soupy.
Fold whipped cream into mixture.
Add celery and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: lemon snowflakes
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cake mix, whipped topping and egg with electric mixer until blended. Batter will be sticky.
Drop by teaspoonful into 10x sugar. Roll to coat. Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: bertha's corn bread
directions: Sift together in large bowl the dry ingredients.
Add the milk and egg and mix well.
Heat muffin cups until oil is hot.
Add mixture and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add grated lemon rind.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder; add to mixture, alternately with milk.
Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in a well-greased loaf pan for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: hot sausage dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add salsa, chili and cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted and mixture is thoroughly heated.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, salt, buttermilk, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup of the chopped Heath bars and nuts; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients and wet ingredients until smooth.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Sprinkle nuts and Heath bars on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: louisiana yum-yum
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mary's homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken in large pot for 1 hour, or sooner if tender. Remove chicken from pot.
Add remaining ingredients to boiled chicken broth.
Cut-up chicken and add to broth.
Add noodles. Homemade noodles are great with this recipe.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Add ingredients to suit taste.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add other ingredients except beef broth.
Mix. Brown in hot fat.
Add beef broth and 1/2 cup of water; pour over meatballs and simmer 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-filled cake
directions: Prepare box cake mix according to directions, using an angel food cake pan.
Let cake cool.
Keeping top whole, slice off 1 inch from top; place aside.
Scoop out center of ring.
Place cake pieces in bowl and sprinkle with brandy.
Fill center of cake with pastry filling, alternating with cake pieces.
Reset top of cake. Smooth over entire cake with whipped cream topping.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: chili con queso
directions: Simmer in saucepan all vegetables until tender.
Stir in cream cheese; add Tabasco and chili powder.
For a more cheesy taste, add 4 ounces mild cheddar cheese and a little white wine.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water. Blend well.
Grease two 9 x 5-inch bread pans and dust lightly with flour.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line 10 1/2 x 15-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Cover with a single layer of saltines.
Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan and add the brown sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over saltines. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Pour chocolate chips over while still hot and let melt.
Spread until smooth.
Place in freezer until hard.
Break up and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add carrots.
Bake in large loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: weight watchers pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in skillet.
Add pepper rings, onion rings and can of tomatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
No other seasoning is needed.
The tomatoes from the skillet are good on a baked potato.
No butter is needed.

title: crab pie(serves 16)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake the crusts 3 minutes and cool. Combine eggs, flour, mayonnaise and milk.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold into pie crusts.
Bake for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: punch
directions: Add ice.
Mix well.
May use 1/2 gallon ice cream.

title: laura's cake
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and egg until blended. Don't overmix.
Stir in chips.
Prepare cake according to the box.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Take cake out at 10 minutes and add cheese mixture in large spoonfuls over cake.
Put cake back in oven for remaining time.
(It may need longer.)
Test with a toothpick.
Refrigerate.

title: crusty oven baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a shallow bowl, combine egg, water and salt.
Dip fish fillets into egg mixture and then coat generously with crushed cereal.
Place on a foil-lined baking sheet.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or just until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with lemon juice.

title: vermont maple syrup frosting
directions: Beat egg whites in small bowl until forms firm peaks.
In the meantime, boil 1 cup syrup in heavy pan on medium heat until forms a soft ball.
Pour syrup very slowly into beaten egg whites at high speed until blended thoroughly.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Heat cooker.
Add shortening and flour and make a brown roux. Then add all the green ingredients; add water (2 quarts).
You may add more water.
Cook for 1 hour after it begins to boil.

title: baked chicken with pineapple
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and roll in flour. Brown on both sides in fat.
Combine cream of chicken soup and pineapple and pour into baking dish.
Place chicken sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use sauce as gravy for vegetables served with chicken.
For more moist chicken, pour sauce over chicken.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and onion rings.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle on the onion rings and bake for 10 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
This serves 10 people.

title: fried chicken
directions: Batter chicken with flour.
Add seasoned salt and onion salt. Fry chicken in butter-flavor Crisco oil until golden brown.
Fry over medium heat.

title: microwaved mashed potatoes
directions: In microwave bowl with lid (my preference is clear Pyrex), place potatoes with water.
Cook on full power for 13 minutes, stirring thoroughly once halfway through cooking time.
Place margarine in bowl; leave covered for 3 to 4 minutes.
Mash potatoes well.
Add milk slowly for desired consistency.
Serve with more margarine, salt and pepper.
Serves family of 5 well.

title: "philly" 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fresh fruit or cherry pie filling.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut up carrots and cook a little, not done. Mix carrots, onions and diced bell pepper into a large bowl and pour in the tomato soup, sugar, mustard, Worcestershire, vinegar and oil. Marinate for 12 hours.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini in margarine slowly until transparent.
Cool and add vinegar, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Put in double crust and bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour together.
Add sweet milk and stir. Put on low to medium heat.
Cook until it gets hot.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat egg yolks in a bowl.
Put some hot mix with eggs and beat, then pour in mix.
Cook until it gets thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: cereal cheese squares
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Turn out onto very lightly floured rectangle (8 x 6-inch and about 3/8-inch thick).
Cut with knife in 1-inch squares.
Remove each square carefully and place 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool onto rack.
Store airtight.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Combine ingredients; chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy-mustard cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender; put in casserole and top with dressing.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Add to shortening mix.
Add fruit cocktail.
Bake at 350°.
Makes a 2 layer cake.

title: easy cheese and broccoli soupeverton, missouri
directions: Melt butter in 3 qt. saucepan. Add onion and celery.
Cook and stir 5 minutes over medium heat.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Sprinkle rosemary and black pepper over chicken.
Bake in a covered roasting pan at 400° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with wild rice and asparagus.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into salt water.
Cover and cook until tender; drain well.
Mash or beat with beater.
Add remaining ingredients.
(May add 2 tablespoons chopped chives, if desired.) Place in large casserole dish and dab with more butter.
Sprinkle with paprika for garnish.

title: cheesy scallop soup
directions: Melt butter and cook onion until tender, covered.
Stir in flour and add milk, cooking until it bubbles.
Add scallops, mushrooms, salt and pepper, simmering, 15 to 20 minutes.
Add wine and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Top with parsley and serve. Very easy and tasty on a cold day.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter until transparent.
Add vegetable mixture to combined bread crumbs and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Yields 10 cups.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients except cake mix and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mix in pan.
On top of this, sprinkle chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, no longer.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients; spoon into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sliced green onion and chopped tomato.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: double dip bonbons
directions: Mix the margarine, vanilla and rest of ingredients, except chocolate chips and paraffin.
Mix well.
Form into small balls; set aside.
Melt wax and chocolate chips over hot water in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate and coat completely.
Place on wax paper.
Dip again for richer bonbons.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients, being generous with the garlic powder.
Simmer all until noodles are done.
Stir it frequently to keep from sticking.
Serves 4 generously.
Leftovers are microwavable if larger batch is desired.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes.
Soak in salt water in refrigerator overnight (minimum of 6 hours).
Drain and place in saucepan.
Cover with water.
Simmer until tender; drain.
Soak bread crumbs in evaporated and whole milk; set aside.
Melt butter and saute onions, green pepper, and celery until tender.
Combine egg-plant, bread crumb mixture, and sauteed vegetables.
Add eggs, pimiento and seasonings.
Blend thoroughly.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven just until the cheese melts.

title: backyard bean salad
directions: Combine beans, eggs, celery, onion and enough dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Season to taste; chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dump-it cake(serves 12)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump 1 can sweetened applesauce into it.
Dump 1 can crushed pineapple on top of that.
Spread 1 package of dry yellow cake mix over that.
Melt 1 cup of butter or margarine and pour over the cake mix.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts over the butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl with spoon.
Pour into flour and greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the apples, eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, blending well.
Add a few drops of green food coloring to desired color.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: chewy cheese bars
directions: Melt butter and combine with cake mix and pecans.
Put into a 9x3 inch baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and cream cheese together. Spread over top of cake mixture.
Sprinkle pecans over the top. Bake in oven at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together all ingredients except 2 tablespoons of oats.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of oats on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 18.

title: chop suey
directions: Saute meat until brown in shortening; add water and celery, simmer 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch into soy sauce and add meat mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes. Add mushrooms and bean sprouts and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: stella's quick meal
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain well.
Add soups and picante sauce.
Serve on buns, over rice or with fried potatoes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Stir in macaroni and 1 1/2 cups of the cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.

title: ham and sweet potatoes in sauce
directions: Chop ham and potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Heat the oil and butter in Dutch oven.
Add sweet potatoes and saute until lightly brown, add thawed onions, saute for 2 minutes.
Remove potatoes and onions from the pan, mix flour with drippings, whisking constantly for 2 minutes.
Gradually add the mandarin juice, chopped mandarin peel, and stock.
Cook this mixture until thickened, add potatoes, onions, broccoli and ham.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes until the vegetables are tender and the ham is heated through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spiced cranberry-orange dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in large bowl. Stir in next 6 ingredients and refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until a spoon drawn through leaves a definite impression.
Stir in orange slices, pineapple and walnuts and chill for 3 to 4 hours.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Drain.
Add green beans and soup. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes and whip with a little milk and margarine.
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on top.
Makes 4 servings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat 3 minutes.
Add eggs and both flavorings.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: creole meat seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in a covered container. Sprinkle meat well with this seasoning before cooking.
This is good on anything:
hamburgers, pork chops, chicken or steak (any kind of meat).

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil fryer until fork-tender.
Remove to cool.
Save chicken broth.
Discard skin and bones and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Put back into broth on low fire.

title: watergate cake with impeachment icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together, on high, 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cornflake balls
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and peanut butter in heavy sauce pan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour in cornflakes and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon
until crisp.
Drain, then crumble.	Reserve 2 tablespoons
bacon	drippings.
Combine
spinach, mushrooms, tomatoes and onion	in
a
large mixing bowl. Combine vinegar, sugar, salt,
pepper,
mustard,
drippings	and
2 tablespoons water in saucepan.	Heat
to just boiling.	Pour dressing over salad. Toss lightly.
Garnish with bacon. Serve immediately.

title: chicken parmesan i
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter; dip chicken in butter, then dip top of chicken in crumbs.
Place in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining butter over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Do not turn chicken while baking.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, finely chopped dill or sweet pickle or relish, finely chopped onion, snipped parsley, chopped pimento and lemon juice.
Cover; chill for several hours.
Makes 1 cup.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook cubed squash, onion and 1 1/2 cups water until squash is tender. Drain and mash squash.
Add poultry seasoning, salt, pepper, chicken soup and cornbread.
Mix well.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbling and brown.
Very good.

title: santa fe quiche appetizers
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in a 7 x 11-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes approximately 36.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir all together in a pot and simmer, uncovered, until sauce is thick, approximately 3 to 5 hours. Makes 1 quart.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Mix dressing of oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Marinate vegetables in dressing overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Mix until smooth.
Butter 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn mixture into pan.
Spoon pie filling into cake in spots evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Place bottom side up on serving plate.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Crush bananas and whip until very light.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour, soda and nuts.
Add bananas.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Roll pastry about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in 5-inch squares.
Mix the sliced apples, brown sugar, cinnamon and 2 spoons sugar together.

title: seafood medley
directions: To batter, mix all seafood in a large bowl. Sprinkle crumbs over and mix with your hands.
Lift from the sides until pieces have some coating. Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine in large casserole dish.
Put in battered seafood.
Cover dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tortilla roll-up
directions: Place margarine, poppy seed and mustard in 6 ounce custard cup. Microwave uncovered on High (100%) until margarine is melted, 30 to 40 seconds; stir until margarine is smooth.
Spread on tortillas. Place ham on tortillas; sprinkle with cheese.
Roll tortillas around ham.
Wrap each tortilla in microwavable paper towel. Microwave on High (100%) until hot, 1 to 1 1/4 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: spinach salad with spicy honey dressing
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine the spinach, mushrooms, tomatoes, celery, bean sprouts, cheese, sunflower kernels and seasonings.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Note:
You may substitute 1 can chow mein vegetables for 1 can of the soup.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix egg yolks and sugar together; heat until very creamy. Sift flour and baking powder; add to nuts and dates.
Fold into the egg yolk mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold into all of mixture.
Bake in a low temperature oven, 275°, until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pat into greased 9 x 13 pan. Mixture will be very dry. Mix confectioners sugar, eggs and cream cheese. Pour over bottom layer. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Let cool. Cut into squares.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika, salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, brown chicken strips. Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook until tender. Add tomatoes and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice, then remove from heat and cover.
Let set until all liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: grits souffle
directions: Follow grits instructions, making with water.
While hot, melt stick of butter and garlic cheese, blend in beaten eggs and finish filling with milk.
Mix and put in hot and buttered casserole dish; crush croutons to top casserole.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes; serve while hot.

title: cool whip fruit salad(9 x 13-inch or 8 x 12-inch pan)
directions: Mix all ingredients with an electric mixer, adding lemon juice last.
Spread in pan.
Top with crushed walnuts and cherry halves. Refrigerate to set.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan and heat, then remove from heat. Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved well. Cool. Stir in buttermilk. Fold in Cool Whip and pecans. Add coconut, if desired. Chill. Serves 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with 1 crust.
Combine other ingredients and add to crust.
Put the top crust on and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: california apple hill cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices.
Mix dry ingredients with sugar mixture and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in preheated oven.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry bacon; melt butter.
Cap, wash and air dry mushrooms. Combine cream cheese, bacon, chives and salt to taste.
Dip mushrooms in melted butter.
Fill with cream cheese mixture. Place under broiler until bubbly and brown.
This can be cooked in a sheet pan or casserole dish.

title: chili pie
directions: Heat chili for 2 to 3 minutes or until hot.
Pour chili on top of Fritos.
Sprinkle desired amount of cheese on top and serve.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix margarine, milk, sugar and cocoa powder together; boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats and vanilla.
Stir together and pour onto waxed paper; let cool.
Work fast because it sets up quickly.
Break or cut into pieces.
Store airtight. You may also add 1/2 cup coconut or 1/2 cup peanut butter.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In sauce pan cook mushrooms and onions with 1/4 c. butter 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove vegetables, leaving butter in sauce pan; set vegetables aside.
Blend flour, chicken bouillon, salt, nutmeg and pepper into sauce pan.
Add milk; cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in mushrooms, onions, asparagus, pimiento and lemon juice.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: cherry pineapple jubilee
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Put chopped nuts over margarine.
Add pineapple over nuts.
Add pie filling over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over pie filling.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook and stir onions, celery, green peppers and garlic in butter until tender.
Remove from heat; add tomato sauce, water and remaining seasonings.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Add more water if needed.
Stir in shrimp. Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook over medium heat 10 to 20 minutes or until shrimp are pink and tender.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: appetizer party pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and beef together, breaking it apart with fork.
Drain any excess fat.
Add spices and cubed cheese
to mixture
and
mix well.
Spread on party rye while warm.
Cool and freeze on cookie sheet.
When frozen, place in freezer bag until ready to use.

title: plea bargain pasta salad
directions: Make a bed of lettuce on a large plate or platter.
Gently toss pasta shells, peas and carrots with the Italian salad dressing.
Pour into the center of the bed of lettuce.
Garnish with tomato wedges and sprinkle all with Parmesan cheese.
Chill.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Blend cream cheese, butter and sugar with medium speed mixer.
Blend in eggs on low speed.
Combine cake flour and baking powder; add to cheese mixture and blend until smooth.
Pour into buttered and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes, until golden brown.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.
Serves 12.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook beef over medium heat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package; drain.
Spoon enough sauce mixture into 7 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish to cover bottom.
Lay half of noodles on, top with half of cottage cheese and cover with sauce. Repeat layer.
Lay Mozzarella cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cut in chunks.
Mix with undiluted soup, sour cream and pimento.
Top with cheese and bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: farfel souffle
directions: In large bowl, mix beaten eggs, sugar, butter and salt.
Hold aside apples and raisins. Place farfel in strainer and run cold water over it.
Fold farfel mixture into egg mixture.
Place one layer of farfel mixture in pan that has been greased (rectangular pan is best), then one layer of apples and raisins.
The rest of farfel.
Dot with butter, bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hours.

title: delicious lunch or dinner omelette
directions: Melt margarine in skillet or omelette pan.
Cover entire bottom and heat to medium.
Mix remaining ingredients, except salsa sauce.
Pour mixture into skillet.
Tilt pan so entire bottom is evenly covered.
When mixture become firm on bottom, use a spatula to gently lift up from bottom side.
When cooked through flip over with spatula or, if using omelette pan, close lid and flip over and brown lightly to a golden brown.
Sprinkle lightly with salsa sauce.
Can be served with hash brown potatoes or toast with jelly or jam, bacon or sliced ham.

title: hot tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook until thick.
Put in jars and seal.
It will be thin and soupy at first, but keep cooking. Have the heat high enough for it to boil good.
Keep it stirred.

title: easy cherry cake
directions: Cook in 9 x 12 or 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Put can of pie filling on bottom.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over top.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all items together and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with any kind of fruit.

title: bloody mary
directions: Over ice cubes in 10-ounce highball glass, measure all ingredients, except lime wedge.
Squeeze lime wedge into mixture; stir well.

title: holiday dressing
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Cook onion and celery in butter or margarine until tender.
Mix stuffing, poultry seasoning, salt and black pepper.
Stir in broth, celery, onion, butter and sausage. Mix well.
Stuff 14 to 20 pound turkey lightly.
Do not overstuff. Dressing may be baked separately for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake(bread)
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into tube or loaf pan that has been greased and floured.
May use Pam instead to prepare pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Done when cake springs back to touch.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: greek fritters(tiganites)
directions: Sift flour in a
bowl.	Add
baking
powder
and
salt. Stir in the milk.
In another
bowl,
beat
the	eggs with the sugar until thick.
Add to the flour mixture; add the vanilla. Beat well with wire whisk;
batter
should be thick.	Heat the oil in a deep pan.
Drop	batter	by
large spoonful into oil. When golden brown,
turn over.	Do not pierce them.
Remove to a platter. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or honey.

title: praline strips
directions: Arrange graham crackers in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Place butter and sugar in saucepan.
Heat to boiling point, boil 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans; spread evenly over crackers.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Cut each cracker in half while still warm. Makes 48 strips.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Cook chicken flavored rice according to package directions, omitting butter.
Cool.
Mix reserved artichoke liquid with the mayonnaise.
Mix chopped onions, bell pepper, olives, artichoke hearts and curry powder with the reserved marinated liquid, mayonnaise and rice.
Garnish with sliced ripe olives. Refrigerate.
Serves 6.

title: greek lemon soup(serves 4)
directions: Combine broth and rice in 3-quart covered casserole.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Let stand covered 20 minutes.
Combine lemon peel, lemon juice and egg.
Pour small amount of hot broth into egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Return to hot broth.
Heat in covered casserole, but do not boil, 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve immediately in individual soup bowls, topped with slice of lemon and garnished with parsley.

title: chicken breasts with chipped beef
directions: Layer dried beef in 8 x 11-inch casserole.
Wrap bacon around chicken pieces and place on top of dried beef.
Mix up sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Scrub and slice cucumbers.
Peel and thinly slice onions. Sprinkle with salt.
Mix well.
Cover bowl and let stand 3 hours. Rinse vegetables with cold water and drain thoroughly.
Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Pour brine over veggies.
Mix and cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Pack in straight-sided containers.
Cover with brine.
Leave 1-inch headspace.
Seal and freeze.
Defrost 8 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool.
Break into bite sized pieces.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan and line with Doritos.
Place chicken pieces on Doritos.
Heat butter, soup (no water), cheese, onion and Ro-Tel in double boiler or microwave until cheese melts, stirring frequently.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese together.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Pour cheese and butter mix into sugar mix and set in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: aloe vera salve
directions: Melt the Vaseline.
Add the chopped aloe vera stems.
Heat until it foams up good; cool.
Repeat until you do it 3 times, then add a little sulfur.
Strain.
Good for rashes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Add canned foods and milk.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pour over chips.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven long enough to melt the cheese.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Cook peas and drain.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cashew-chicken hot dish
directions: Mix all and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: barbecue chicken packets
directions: You will need four sheets of 12 x 18-inch aluminum foil.

title: peach conserve
directions: Grind all together.
Add 1 cup sugar for each cup pulp. Let stand
overnight.
Boil
minutes
in heavy pan.
Makes approximately 10 to 12 jelly glasses.

title: good goulash
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Cook noodles separately; drain and set aside.
Combine meat and rest of ingredients, except noodles.
Simmer until celery is tender (about 20 to 30 minutes). Add noodles; mix well.
Serve.

title: smoothie shake
directions: Peel and slice banana.
Add pineapple juice, powdered milk and yogurt.
Add crushed ice.
Add to blender and blend briefly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together thoroughly except the tomato sauce. Pat into a loaf pan. If you like bacon favor you can cover with 2 strips of bacon and then pour the can of tomato sauce over the meat loaf and bacon. Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees. Serves six.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle lemon juice over salmon.
In a medium size bowl, combine milk, bread crumbs, eggs, onion, salt, pepper and parsley.
Pour over salmon and blend well.
Pour into a greased, microwave-safe loaf pan.
Heat, uncovered, on full power 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Place on serving platter. Serves 4 to 6.
I halve this.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until tender; remove from bones. Combine bread crumbs, onions and 1/2 egg and giblets in large mixing bowl.
Pour broth over ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish and place chicken and remaining egg over mixture. Pour cream of chicken soup over mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Stir jelly and chili sauce together.
Let cook until both are dissolved.
Add wieners. Simmer until heated (approximately 1 hour). Or mix all ingredients and cook in crock-pot approximately 2 to 3 hours.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Scald milk.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually stir into scalded milk; add coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Wash them and pat them dry.
Cook sausage; crumble it and place on paper towel to drain.
Add package of Mozzarella cheese to sausage.
Then in a microwave-safe dish, melt the margarine.
Add garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Gently coat (not cook) mushrooms with Parmesan cheese mixture and stuff with sausage and Mozzarella cheese mixture.
Bake or use microwave only long enough to melt cheese mixture.

title: cape may point crab
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
In a casserole, cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot and crumbs are browned (about 45 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: dixie house baked squash
directions: Cut and boil squash about 10 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Mash to remove remaining liquid.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in melted margarine, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: Mix soup, onions, sour cream, chilies and salt.
Add chicken and milk.
Layer Doritos, soup mixture and then grated cheese. Repeat, ending with grated cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter until transparent.
Add mushrooms.
Slice beef thin and roll in flour.
Add to onion and mushrooms and any remaining flour.
Let this brown 5 to 10 minutes over medium heat. Add beef broth.
Cook 1 hour.
Keep checking to avoid sticking. Remove from heat and add sour cream and cooked noodles.

title: magic goop("play dough")
directions: Mix salt and water.
Heat over low heat. Add cornstarch and cold water to heated mixture. Stir mixture until it becomes a smooth, pliant ball. (Reheat slowly, if necessary.)
Cool before giving to children and supervise its use. Dye white dough with nontoxic food colorings and store in airtight plastic bags.
Goop will dry to a hard finish when exposed to air for approximately 48 hours.

title: banana split delight
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter; pour into crumbs.
Press into deep pan for crust.
Beat at high speed 5 to 10 minutes the softened stick of butter, powdered sugar and eggs.
Place a layer of bananas, a layer of pineapple and a layer of bananas.
Pour powdered sugar mixture over layers.
Let sink into layers good.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish; spread peaches on top of margarine.
Pour mixture of flour, sugar and milk (mixed well together) on top of peaches.
Bake at 300° until cobbler is golden brown.

title: walking taco
directions: Layer in order given; serve with tortilla chips.

title: prawns in garlic-tomato sauce
directions: In large nonstick frying pan, over medium heat, heat the oil. Add frozen shrimp and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain off excess liquid.
Add garlic and onions and saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and oregano, bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, add red pepper flakes and salt and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by rounded teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Marinate cauliflower, onion, leaves, radish and peel in oil and vinegar dressing.
Before serving, pour off dressing and add sour cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish.
Place strips of bacon on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth; drain.
Add cheese very slowly! You may not want quite that much cheese on your recipe, so use your own judgment.
Brown onion and pepper in small amount of margarine.
Mix soup and milk together and add to spaghetti and cheese mixture.
Stir in onion and pepper, then add chicken.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: sambousick
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan.
Add very finely chopped onions and fry until yellow.
Add the meat, stirring to break it up.
Stir in the spices and salt; fry until well brown.
Remove from heat. Mince the green onions and cilantro or parsley; stir into the meat mixture.
Set aside.

title: vera's shrimp
directions: Peel and clean shrimp.
Saute shrimp, onion, celery and bell pepper in butter or margarine on low heat for 10 minutes or until shrimp are tender. Add mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes longer. Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper.
Blend well. Stir in sour cream and cream cheese. Cook gently for 10 minutes (allowing cream cheese to melt), not allowing mixture to boil. Serve over hot rice or fettucini noodles.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Sift
together
flour
and baking powder.
Mix together eggs, brown sugar, candy orange slices, flour mixture, pecans, vanilla and
orange
juice.
Spread in buttered pan.
Bake in slow
oven. When
done,
have
ready powdered sugar, juice of orange and melted
butter.
Spread
on while hot.
Cut any way desired.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh fruit dressing
directions: Put all ingredients, except poppy seed, in blender; mix well. Stir in poppy seed.
Chill; stir before using.
Makes 2 cups. This is so easy, and with so much less oil than most dressings of this type.
It's acceptable for those watching their fat intake. Plus, it's delicious!

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix the above ingredients together and serve with sliced apples.

title: broccoli with honey and mustard
directions: Blanch or steam broccoli.
To make sauce, mix water with mustard, honey and pepper.
Toss 1/2 cup of sauce with broccoli and serve.

title: chilled mexican appetizer
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; spread mixture in 12-inch round platter with sides.
Combine chopped avocados, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Toss and arrange evenly over bean mixture.
Set aside. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Spoon over avocado mixture.
Combine green pepper and next 3 ingredients. Sprinkle over sour cream mixture.
Top vegetable mixture with cheese.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and green onions.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yields about 12 cups.

title: cabbage bake
directions: Butter an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ingredients in pan.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: barbecued sausage and noodles
directions: Cook 1/2 package of egg noodles by directions on package.

title: southern beef and beans casserole
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef, onions and green pepper until meat is browned; drain. Combine meat mixture, Bush's baked beans and tomato paste. Spoon mixture into lightly greased 8-inch baking dish. Prepare muffin mix according to directions. Spread evenly over bean mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream.
Fold into cream cheese, mayo and vanilla (blended together).
Add fruit and nuts to creamy mix.
May be chilled or frozen.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Brown beef, green onions and bell pepper.
Drain off grease.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pan.
Beat milk and Bisquick together with eggs until smooth. Pour into pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning and water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally, then mix in cheese, lettuce, tomato, onion and chips.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and cool.
Blend cream cheese and sugar together.
Beat Milnot until it forms stiff peaks. Combine first 2 mixtures and then add into the whipped milk, mixing well; add vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with a few of the graham cracker crumbs.
Place in the refrigerator and let stand for 24 hours.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk, then add lemon juice and vanilla. Pour mixture in pie shell, then place drained cherries on top. Refrigerate and chill.

title: hot lettuce
directions: Fry or microwave bacon until crisp, then crumble.
In a saucepan or frying pan, combine the sugar, flour, salt and egg. Add vinegar, milk, bacon and one or two tablespoons bacon fat (if desired).
Cook to thicken, stirring constantly.
If too thick, add more milk.
Pour over lettuce, which has been mixed with celery and onion.
Serve at once.

title: venison swiss steak
directions: Prepare venison, quail, dove, duck, goose or pheasant for cooking.
Let stand 2 hours in barbecue sauce, turning several times.
Take from sauce; place in deep skillet or open roasting pan.
Cover with barbecue sauce; cover and simmer (200° to 225°) or leave pan uncovered and cook in moderate oven (325°) until tender, basting occasionally with barbecue sauce.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, add chicken and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Deep fry.

title: radish roses
directions: Cut green tops of radishes.
Make 6 to 8 cuts down the side of each radish, from tip to stem end.
Thus the petals will form. Make sure cuts are thick enough not to break easily.
Place in ice water for 1hour or more so the petals will curl like roses.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all. Top with additional cheese and crackers and dots of butter. Brown in moderate oven.

title: peach jam
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to full rolling bowl and boil for 40 minutes.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Turn off heat, add butter and stir until melted.
Pour into jars and seal.
Yield: Approximately 16 cups.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Heat broth, pepper, soy sauce and sesame oil until it begins to boil. Put corn starch is small dish, add a tiny bit of water, make a paste and stir into broth. Stir to thicken. Whisk egg, and using a fork, drizzle over boiling soup. Reduce heat to keep warm until ready to serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Gradually add flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook together raisins and water until about 5 tablespoons liquid remains; drain and save liquid. I usually save more than 5 tablespoons liquid; you may need more than 5 tablespoons. You can tell when you get it all mixed up.

title: date balls
directions: Chop pitted dates.
Add sugar, margarine and nuts.
Cook for 2 to 5 minutes until thickened.
Allow to cool.
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oranges with juice, eggs and oil in a mixer about 3 minutes.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt cheese with soup and milk; add chiles.
Dip tortillas in broth where chicken breasts were cooked.
Sprinkle with cheese and chicken pieces.
Roll and place side by side in casserole, 9 x 12 x 24-inches.
Cover with sauce.
Top with more grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 14 enchiladas.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen.
Excellent for buffets.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut bread into half-inch wide strips.
Arrange in layers in buttered baking dish.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and pour over bread.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: 5 spice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; rinse and drain.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Microwave for 18 to 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese and sliced black olives.
This can also be baked in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry torte
directions: Blend
cake
mix, crackers and margarine until crumbly. Add egg and beat until blended.
Press into 12-inch pizza pan. Bake 15 to
minutes at 350° (or until golden brown).
Let cool completely.
Beat
cream cheese until fluffy.
Spread on crust. Then
spread
cherry
pie
filling
over cream cheese, leaving about
inch
cream
cheese showing.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds and refrigerate.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, onion and green pepper. Mix well.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Layer noodles, process cheese spread and meat mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole; cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with additional cheese, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add rest of ingredients; stir well. Simmer on stove for 20 to 30 minutes.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.

title: caramel pecans
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients and boil 3 minutes. Remove from stove. Stir in vanilla and pecans. Pour on paper and pull apart when cool.

title: potato dish casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix the sour cream, soup, pepper, dried onion, cheese, salt and bouillon.
Add potatoes.
Melt butter; mix with corn flakes.
Put potato mixture in a 3-quart casserole dish. Cover with the corn flakes mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lumpia
directions: Gravy:
Mix soy sauce, cornstarch, salt and pepper.

title: quick skillet supper
directions: In large skillet brown meat and drain.
Stir in seasoning, Veg-All vegetables, bouillon and macaroni.
Bring mix to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring 2 times during cooking time.
Stir in sour cream and 1/2 of the French fried onions.
Heat through, do not boil.
Top with remaining French fried onions.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: puttin' on the ritz
directions: Set aside enough pecans to sprinkle tops of crackers.
Mix dates, milk, and pecans.
Cook over medium heat until mixture starts thickening and dates are cooked.
Spread on Ritz crackers. Bake on 350 degrees for a few minutes.
Cool.
Spread with cream cheese icing.
Top with pecans.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together, except for corn flakes and margarine.
Put into baking dish.
Mix together corn flakes and butter.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: egg casserole
directions: Remove	crust
and
place
bread in bottom of greased 2 quart casserole.	Place
meat
evenly
on top of bread.
Beat eggs, milk
and salt together.
Pour over bread.	Refrigerate overnight. Cook, uncovered, for 40 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry - cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add cranberry sauce, stir until thoroughly mixed. Refrigerate until partly set. Add pineapple and pecans and stir. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan and refrigerate over night.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Allow to cool while you sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs to sugar-butter mixture, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and fold in chips and nuts.

title: moist oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, pour boiling water over oats and butter; let stand 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Spread with Brown Sugar Topping.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Tear into bite-size pieces and place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers and poppy seed and sprinkle over chicken and soup.
Melt oleo and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° until hot throughout, about 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: coconut flake cookies
directions: Add corn flakes to sifted dry ingredients.
Cream shortening; add sugars and blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add vanilla, then flour and corn flake mixture.
Mix well.
Add coconut.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: bible cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake in a greased pan at 350° until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onions, mushrooms and beef in butter in electric frypan. Add both cans of soup.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin and mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water to the first mixture.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Stand 10 minutes before taking out of pans.

title: tourtiere(pork pie)
directions: Combine meats, onion, salt and water.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Add spices; cook 15 minutes longer.
Let stand to let flavors blend.
Cook potatoes.
Mash while hot; mix immediately with meat mixture.
Place in a pie shell.
Cover with top shell; lattice style if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until nicely browned.
When cooled, may be stored in freezer, wrapped in tinfoil or adequate freezer bag.
A delightful dish.
Always draws compliments from guests and family.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix altogether and roll in crushed cracker crumbs.
Shape into ball and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: brussels sprouts in sauce
directions: Wash sprouts thoroughly and remove discolored leaves.
Cut off stem ends and slash bottom of each with a shallow X.
Place sprouts in a small amount of boiling water.
Cover and simmer 8 minutes over low heat or until sprouts are tender.
Drain and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small saucepan; cook 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Pour sauce mixture over sprouts.
Toss well.
Serves 4.

title: tutti-frutti cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add well beaten egg, vinegar and vanilla.
Put soda in milk.
Sift flour and cocoa.
Add alternately the flour and milk into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and dates or raisins. Bake in three (9-inch) pans in 325° oven until done.
Stack with crushed pineapple and whipped topping. Use juice to moisten the cake.
Add a layer of pineapple and cream to each layer.
Can be frozen (refrigerated).

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Add this mixture to the Jell-O and stir until well mixed.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour into dish and chill until set.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pour in unbaked shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 425°.

title: aunt alacia's chocolate oat nut cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Put oats in a bowl.
Stir in boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in butter, brown and granulated sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Beat in flour mixture and mix well.
Fold in 1/2 the chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Stone cherries and drain (save juice).
Heat cherry juice and dissolve gelatin in it.
Add lemon juice and sherry; cool.
When it starts to thicken, add nuts and cherries.

title: pollo de puerto vallarta
directions: Wrap all chicken breasts in foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Make sauce of soups, milk, onion and salsa.
Alternate layers of chicken, sauce and tortillas in greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 24 hours (important!).
Cook (heat through) at 300° for 1 hour or so.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti in a large amount of salted water for 10 to 12 minutes or just until tender. Drain. Stir margarine into hot spaghetti. Stir in beaten eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a greased 10-inch pie plate. Spread with cottage cheese.

title: persian salad dressing
directions: Put this all together in a blender. Whip until it is thick and creamy. Makes 1 quart.

title: blueberry mousse
directions: Wash berries and pat dry.
Put in blender and puree.
Reserve a few berries to use as garnish.
Dissolve gelatin in water according to package directions.
Beat egg yolks with sugar in a medium saucepan.
In another medium saucepan, bring milk to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour into egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Place egg-milk in saucepan on heat; continue cooking (do not boil) until mixture is thickened, stirring constantly. Stir gelatin and pureed berries into hot mixture; let cool.
When mixture begins to set, fold in whipped cream.
Toss a few reserved berries into mold, then add mixture.
Garnish top with a few more berries.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: moist and delicious fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in two 9-inch layers. Split layers in half to make 4 thin layers. Combine sour cream, powdered sugar and 1 cup of the coconut. Spread filling equally on cut side of each layer. Frost top and sides of cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle with the remaining coconut. Refrigerate immediately. Make 2 days in advance for moister cake.

title: spicy meatballs
directions: Peel and
finely
chop	the
onion.
Peel and crush the garlic.
Put
with rest of ingredients except for the oil in a bowl and
mix
well
together.
Shape mixture into walnut size balls.
Fry the meatballs in shallow oil for about 15 minutes, turning once.
Arrange
on	a
warmed
serving plate and serve with rice or pasta and a tomato sauce or gravy.

title: easy mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger, mix together taco sauce, kidney beans and 1/2 Fritos.
Add hamburger, put into 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle remaining Fritos on casserole.
Sprinkle cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken delicious
directions: Put a little oil in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chicken and vegetables in pan.
Mix all seasoning.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, pumpkin, sugar and vanilla. Add the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dottie thirkel's dumplings
directions: Beat like crazy.
It'll be gooey.
Drop in spoonfuls on top of completely cooked boiled chicken in 8-quart pan.
Broth should barely cover the chicken.
Gently boil 5 minutes.
Put lid on pan. Steam 5 minutes more.
Serve.
May top with gravy made from chicken broth.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Mix potato soup according to directions on can. Add steamed broccoli, dash of parsley and 1 tablespoon butter. Heat and serve.

title: brown 'n beautiful yams
directions: Peel and cook fresh yams and divide into quarters.
Drain water and place in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter, cinnamon, nutmeg, sugar and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Add mushrooms, rice, consomme and garlic.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into balls. Freeze.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: justin's cherry, pineapple, banana pie
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple, reserving juices.
Add enough water to the reserved juices to equal 2 cups.
Combine juices with cherries, pineapple, salt, sugar, flour and coloring in saucepan. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Fold in bananas and pecans.
Pour into pie shells.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, layer: lettuce, carrots, mushrooms, peas, 2 cups mayonnaise, cheeses (combined) and bacon bits.

title: cheesy chicken bake
directions: Arrange chicken tenders in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine the soup and 1/2 cup water; stir well.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Crush stuffing mix and add seasoning packet.
Mix together.
Sprinkle crumbs over cheese.
Melt margarine and drizzle over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bean crock-pot soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In large crock-pot, mix all ingredients.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours, or until beans are done.

title: crispy duck
directions: Mix salt, Accent and white pepper.
Defrost the duck first. Rinse inside and outside of duck and let it dry for half an hour. Rub mixture evenly on the duck and inside the cavity.
Put duck in the refrigerator for about 24 hours.

title: christmas candy
directions: Preheat oven 325°
for	glass
dish,
350° for regular. Put butter in dish
and
melt
in
oven.
Add
graham
cracker crumbs. Mix and
press
flat
into butter.
Pour cream evenly over crust. Add a
layer
of chocolate chips, then a layer of coconut and finally a
layer of crushed pecans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, according to required oven temperature.

title: cauliflower and tomatoes(microwave)
directions: In a 1-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine cauliflower, onions and water.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 5 to 7 minutes or until cauliflower is crisp-tender. Drain well.

title: onion-mushroom meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients plus 2 Tbsp. ketchup (except bacon slices).
Form into a loaf.
Cover with ketchup.
Lay bacon on top.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn dog bites
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir in bacon drippings.
Combine egg, buttermilk and soda; mix well.
Stir into flour mixture, mixing well.
Cut each frankfurter into 10 pieces.
Dip frankfurter sections into batter, covering completely.
(Wooden picks work well for dipping.)
Drop into 3 to 4 inches deep hot oil (375°) and cook until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
