Insert party picks and serve immediately.
Serve with mustard, catsup or picante sauce, if desired.

title: instant fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges; throw away juice.
Drain pineapple; save juice. Mix fruit and sliced bananas in a large bowl.
Sprinkle instant pudding over fruit.
Pour pineapple juice over mixture; fold until pudding is dissolved.
Garnish with cherries.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown your hamburger meat with the chopped onion.
Drain the fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Then cover and simmer; the longer the better.
This is not as spicy as you think it would be.
It is very good.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients into sweet potatoes; spoon into a buttered casserole.

title: whole wheat pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix together first 7 dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Mix together sugar, egg white, vanilla and pumpkin.
Combine milk and oil together; mix alternately with the dry ingredients.
Then stir in raisins and chopped walnuts.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook limas, green peas and green beans separately and season to taste. Drain. Mix all three with mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onion, lemon juice, chestnuts and mayonnaise. Put all in casserole dish and cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until bread crumbs are brown or until mixture is hot.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into a well-greased and floured cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and sifted dry ingredients.
Add oats, coconut and gumdrops, cut up.
Form into small balls and press slightly.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (hot).
Grease baking sheet.
Mix fat and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and lemon extract.
Mix flour, corn meal, baking powder, nutmeg and salt thoroughly.
Add to creamy mixture.
Stir in raisins; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheet while still warm. Cool on rack.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together chocolate, oleo, corn syrup, vanilla, powdered sugar and milk.
Pour over crackers and pudding.
Place, uncovered, in refrigerator until chocolate hardens.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cocoa.
Combine with other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add egg, vanilla and buttermilk. Add flour.
Roll, cut and the bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix pineapple, hot dogs and beans in 2 quart pan.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes on low heat, stirring occasionally.

title: "sweet" onions
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Add salt, sugar and onions.
Cook until tender.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil. Add onion, tomatoes, salt, pepper and water. Cook over low heat until rice absorbs water and it is dry but not burned.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Take 2 sticks pie crust mix.
Shape into a pizza. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix together the sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add to this the melted butter, vanilla and milk.
Place mixture on the crust and sprinkle with the broken pecans. Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken casserole for company
directions: Put soup in bowl.
Add a little milk until creamy.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spoon a little soup in bottom of pan.
Place the chicken breasts in pan.
Put a piece of Velveeta cheese on each breast.
Cover with rest of soup.
Sprinkle with seasoned croutons.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir well in large pan.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons.

title: maid-rites
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet; break into pieces and crumble as it cooks.
Cook onion with meat.
Season, scoop up with slotted spoon so excess grease can drain off.
Put on hamburger bun that has been toasted.
Eat-em-up partner!
These are popular in Fulton County, Illinois.

title: best ever oatmeal cookies
directions: Cover raisins with water just to cover and simmer until soft. Cool.
Cream
well	white sugar, brown sugar, margarine and eggs. Add salt, vanilla and raisin liquid.
Mix flour and soda;
add
to batter mixing well.
Add cooled raisins to the oatmeal
before adding
to the mix.
Nuts and cinnamon can be added if desired. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Melt butter in a 9 x
13-inch	pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs;
top with coconut flakes and chopped nuts. Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.	Slice into desired size bars.

title: custard(similar to flan)
directions: Melt sugar in small iron skillet until slightly browned.
Add 1/2 cup water and boil until mixture threads.
Pour in old fashioned 1 pound coffee can (or any can with tight fitting lid, 1 pound size) and roll it around until thoroughly coated.
Cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice, onions and peppers until tender.
Add bacon and other ingredients.
Cook over low heat about 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Season chicken.
Melt oleo.
Add Durkee sauce and lemon juice. Put chicken in pan, skin side up.
Pour marinating sauce over chicken.
Let set overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican chili quiche(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Place cheese and chilies in 9 x 9-inch pan.
In blender, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into one-inch squares.
Freezes well.

title: cuban rice and chicken
directions: In skillet, saute onion, pepper and mushrooms in oil until onion is translucent, 4 to 5 minutes.
In saucepan, heat chicken broth to boil.
Add rice, Vigo flavor and color, turmeric, olives, capers, bay leaf and black pepper.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes. Fold in chicken and sauteed vegetables.
Remove bay leaf.
If mixture is too thick, add a little broth or bouillon.
Serve hot with salad and garlic bread.
May substitute pork for chicken.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Melt butter on medium.
Remove from heat; add flour and stir until smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
Return to heat and slowly add 2 cups milk.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Mix with macaroni 1 1/2 cups of grated cheese.
Pour in a greased casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Mix celery soup and 1/2 can of milk.
Warm up slowly, then add cream corn and whole kernel corn (drained and cooled).
Dice 3 small potatoes; add to chowder, stirring very often, on low heat. Add half and half, parsley and chives.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel
and
slice
apples,
enough
to
fill
crust; mix remaining ingredients, pour over apples.
Place pats of butter on top
of
this,
then
put other pie crust on top and punch holes in top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until done.

title: elizabeth pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each.
Add vanilla and coconut extract.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat until well blended.
Bake in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan at 300° until done.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large saucepan and bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes; remove from heat and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and blend lightly.
Chill.
Makes 7 cups.

title: casserole
directions: Cook macaroni following directions on package.
Rinse in cold water and drain.
Brown beef, onion and green pepper in skillet. Stir in flour.
Add tomatoes. Cook until thickens.
Stir in cheese, seasoning and macaroni. Spoon in buttered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Mix celery soup and mushroom soup together; set aside.
Brown beef, drain, put in an 8 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with celery, Worcestershire sauce, onion and cheese.
Cover with soup mixture and arrange Tater Tots on top to cover.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into ice cream freezer and freeze. Makes 1 gallon.

title: potato and sausage patties
directions: Combine in bowl. Shape into patties and fry in skillet until done.
Excellent change of pace for meat for supper.

title: lemonade ice cream pie
directions: Place pie crusts in freezer.
Put softened ice cream, lemonade concentrate and 3/4 of the Cool Whip into a large bowl.
Stir until blended.
Spread 1/2 in each pie crust.
Top each with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze just until topping is firm, then cover airtight with foil or plastic wrap.
Freeze 4 hours or until hard.
Serve garnished with lemon slices.

title: rich year around pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare pumpkin pie according to label recipe for pie (or your favorite pumpkin pie recipe).
Combine walnuts, pineapple and coconut with pie filling; blend well.
Pour in pie shell and bake for 1 hour.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Stir together in a large bowl the sugar and flour; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt together the margarine, cocoa, cooking oil and water.
Bring to a boil over low heat, watching carefully so the cocoa doesn't scorch.
Pour the hot cocoa mixture over the sugar and flour mixture.
Beat the eggs slightly and add.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost while warm with Texas Frosting.

title: tex-mex salad
directions: Toss all ingredients except Parmesan cheese together. Sprinkle with cheese.
You may also add avocados or mushrooms.

title: cheese bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast on 1/4 cup water; let stand 5 minutes.
Scald milk and shortening.
Add sugar and salt; cool.
Add 2 cups flour. Beat smooth.
Grate cheese on dough.
Stir yeast.
Add with 1 cup lukewarm water.
Mix well.
Add 4 cups flour all at once.
Beat smooth.
Make medium soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Place in bowl.
Let rise until double.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together and mix up.
Ready to serve or chill.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix thoroughly in saucepan:
sugar, cornstarch, salt, coconut and egg yolks.
Stir in gradually until smooth a mixture of evaporated milk and water.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Cover and cool thoroughly.
Put into cold 9-inch baked pastry shell.
Spread with meringue.

title: raisin squares(no eggs)
directions: Boil in large saucepan the margarine, sugar, raisins, water and cinnamon for 5 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli spears across bottom of 18 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 1/2-inch pan.
Cut cutlets in half and place them flat on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayo, curry and lemon juice and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cornflakes.
Grate cheese over casserole.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice. Serves 5.

title: salmon cake
directions: Remove and discard salmon bones and skin.
Mash salmon.
Beat egg yolks with milk.
Add celery, onion flakes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir into salmon; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gently fold into salmon mixture.
Spoon into a nonstick 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) for 45 minutes or until firm.
Garnish with sliced egg.
Makes 4 luncheon servings.

title: asparagus-noodle casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer noodles, asparagus and eggs.
Dilute soup with asparagus stock; pour over layers.
Season; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: twinkie pudding
directions: Line 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish with Twinkies.
Mix cold milk with pudding mix.
After pudding mix is ready, spread on Twinkies.
Layer the pineapple and bananas.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Add cherries and nuts.
Make the day ahead and refrigerate.

title: broccoli-sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line uncooked pie shell with double thickness of foil.
Bake in 450° oven for 8 minutes.
Remove foil. Bake 4 to 6 minutes more until golden brown.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Reduce oven to 375°.
Cook sausage and mushrooms in a large skillet about 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Knife test.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Mix with onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix salad dressing, salt, pepper, mustard and lemon juice.
Fold into corn mixture. Chill thoroughly.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil the Irish potato until it is soft.
Pour off excess water, then mash the potato.
Begin adding powdered sugar and beat. Continue adding powdered sugar until a stiff dough is formed.
Take a rolling pin and roll out in powdered sugar.
Roll into a thin rectangular shape.
Spread thin layer of peanut butter evenly over dough.
Roll dough up into a long round log shape.
Cut into slices like divinity.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, pudding mix, sour cream and Cool Whip (except leaving 1/3 for topping).
Layer wafers, bananas and mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rice casserole
directions: Spray Pam on bottom of casserole.
Add all ingredients.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar, cinnamon and pecans in a bowl with a tight lid.
Have butter in a shallow bowl.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip into melted butter and then into dry mixture. Cover, shake and then place biscuit pieces in a Bundt pan (greased).
Continue until all of the biscuits are coated.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool, then put on serving plate.

title: trout with almonds(from switzerland)
directions: Prepare trout.
Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice.
Let rest for a few minutes, then carefully pat dry.
Dredge fish with flour.
Brown in hot skillet until golden on all sides.
Arrange on a preheated platter.
Add wine to drippings and bring to boiling.
Stir in cornstarch mixed with a little wine or water. Season to taste and cook until thickened and smooth.
Lightly brown almonds in a small amount of butter.
Sprinkle over trout and pour the same over all.
Serve with lemon slices and lettuce salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham slice and cranberries
directions: Trim ham and
insert
cloves in fat.
Wash cranberries; dry and mix with
honey.
Pour
over
ham and bake in moderate oven at 350° for
hours or until ham is tender.
Baste occasionally with liquid in pan.
One center slice serves 5 to 7.

title: hairy buffalo reunion style(dedicated to annette eskridge, miss mamie)
directions: Cut fruits into wedges, do not peel.
Put into large tub (we use 14 gallon tub at the reunion).
Squeeze fruit slightly as you put it into the tub.
Put the watermelon in - no rinds.
(Uncle Ronnie has proven that the best way to do this is to use your fingers to squeeze the watermelon out.)

title: soft pan brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Melt butter and add to mixture. Add slightly beaten egg, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into an 8-inch greased pan.
Cook for 30 minutes, until it springs back when lightly touched in center, at 350°.

title: easy brunswick stew(very good!)
directions: Boil onion and potatoes until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rich brownie cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix all ingredients, except whipped cream and chocolate; spread in pan.
Bake about 35 minutes or until top appears dry.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool cake completely.
Top with whipped cream and chocolate.
Refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: hot wings
directions: In a large pot over medium-high heat, place the beans in 3 times their volume of water. Bring to a boil and let boil 10 minutes. Cover; remove from heat and let stand 1 hour. Drain and rinse.

title: pork hocks and beans
directions: Boil hocks in water 20 minutes to get grease off.
Place in crock-pot.
Add Northern beans.
Cook in crock-pot all day or until done.
When almost finished cooking, add can of pork and beans.

title: san francisco sourdough french bread
directions: Combine starter, water, sugar and 3 cups flour in a large nonmetal mixing bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap or a towel; let stand at room temperature 12 hours or overnight.
Combine salt, soda and 1 cup flour.
Stir into dough; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil and continue to do so until soft ball stage.
Add 1 1/4 cups oats for chocolate oatmeal candy. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let form.

title: white bread plus
directions: Sift and add 8 cups of all-purpose flour.
If desired, add 1 teaspoons wheat germ for each cup of flour.

title: cheese and pepper loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine dry ingredients and cheese in a medium bowl. In a small bowl, blend well the buttermilk, eggs and melted butter. Add to dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown or toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove from pan. Cool completely.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap and store in refrigerator. May be heated in microwave.

title: steak-em roll ups
directions: Cook stuffing as directed on package.
Put some on each steak, roll steaks up.
Place in baking dish.
Pour can of gravy over steaks.
Bake at 375° until meat is done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften. Combine it with pineapple (drained well on a paper towel).
Add other ingredients.
Roll in a ball and refrigerate for about 30 minutes. Roll ball in pecans.

title: chocolate dip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Gradually blend in flour.
Chill dough.
Form logs about 1 1/2 inches long. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until delicately browned (about 15 minutes).
Cool cookies.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening.
Dip cookies in melted chocolate; coat with toppings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop celery. Cook broccoli and drain. Saute 1 stick of butter, onion and celery. Melt cheese with mushroom soup and stir. Mix celery and onion with cheese and soup mixture.
Drain and add mushrooms. Put together and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Combine garlic slices and nuts in food processor.
Add basil leaves and olive oil.
Blend until mixture is completely pureed. Add 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and unsalted butter.
Blend well.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers in bottom of pie pan.
Line sides with whole wafers.
Melt margarine and pour over wafers.
Pour milk in bowl and add egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Add juice of lemons and stir until thickened.
Pour over crushed wafers.
Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar for topping and brown lightly. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Makes one thick pie or two thin pies.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine boiling water with instant coffee.
Add sugar; cook until sugar dissolves.
Add vanilla extract, chocolate extract and vodka.
Store in dark bottle.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Spread on flat tortilla shells.
Roll up and then slice into 1/2-inch.
You may add 1 can green chilies (crushed) if you want.

title: surprise chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350° or until bubbling.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool. Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Combine salad oil and sugar; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add the carrots; mix well.
Grease and flour pan and pour in batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: sunny dew
directions: Pour a half of a cup of Mountain Dew into a clear glass, then pour half of a cup of red Kool-Aid in the same glass.
Stir roughly 20 seconds, then have fun drinking.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add enough milk to make
thickening.
Add to heated milk and bring to rolling boil. Pour
slowly
into
beaten
eggs, beating all the time. Add
1 3/4 cups sugar.
Strain into 6 quart ice cream freezer. Add
cream and
vanilla
and
more
cream or milk, if needed. Yields 6 quart freezer.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Cover raisins with water. Boil 20 minutes. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or longer.

title: spoon bread 2
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add boiling water to cornmeal. Add egg, milk mixture and melted butter to the cornmeal mixture. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
This was always served hot with butter and pancake syrup.

title: toll house pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs at high speed until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Add flour and sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Beat in margarine.
Stir in walnuts and morsels.
Pour into pie shell.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Preheat
oven
In medium bowl, combine 1/4 of the soup
with remaining ingredients except water.
Mix thoroughly. Shape
into
patties.
Arrange
in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.	Spoon off fat. Combine
remaining	soup and water.
Spoon over patties. Bake 10 minutes more.

title: batter bread
directions: Boil corn meal and boiling water to a mush.
Separate eggs and beat yolks with milk, salt, sugar, shortening, flour and baking powder.
Add to corn meal mush.
Beat egg whites and fold in last. Bake in 350° to 375° oven.
This makes a very moist and slightly sweet corn bread.

title: broccoli fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini, drain and set aside.
Over medium heat, cook broccoli about 5 minutes and drain.
Melt butter and stir in flour until smooth. Gradually whisk in milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir 2 minutes until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in parmesan and broccoli.
Serve over fettuccini.

title: nasu no karashizuke
directions: *Hot when mustard is mixed into a paste.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Put crushed pretzels in bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese and dry jello together in mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup of strawberries to mixture and mix until strawberries are mashed.
Add sour cream and mayonnaise.
"Add only enough to make mixture firm, not runny." Put the rest of the strawberries in mixture.
Save some for garnish.
Spread mixture over pretzels.
Chill for several hours.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients except topping and put in a casserole dish. Melt butter and mix with remaining crackers.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until crackers are browned.

title: hidden valley ranch buttered popcorn
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients.
Toss with popcorn and serve immediately.

title: old time lemon cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk gradually and stir until smooth. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 10 minutes. Stir a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Combine with remaining hot mixture. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Prepare meringue with egg whites.
Place on pie and brown.

title: corn pie
directions: Dice potatoes and celery.
Cook until not quite finished.
In an oblong casserole dish, put the cooked potato/celery mixture. Add layer of corn, then layer of sliced egg.
Repeat layering. Salt and pepper each layer.
Add liquid from canned corn.
Add milk, if necessary to make enough liquid.
Dot with butter.
Cover with unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until crust is finished.

title: oven-smoked turkey
directions: Rub turkey with liquid smoke.
Mix salt and oil and rub turkey.
Place vegetables in cavity.
In deep
roaster
bake 1 hour at 375°, uncovered.
Mix remaining and
pour over turkey. Lower
heat to 325°.
Cover and bake until
done.
Serve
with sauce.

title: chicken with broccoli
directions: Cut chicken into cubes.
Cut broccoli into flowerets.
Heat 1/4 cup oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Saute the chicken with the garlic, shallot, salt and pepper until lightly browned.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer the chicken to a large platter.
Add the remaining 1/4 cup of olive oil to the pan (if needed).
Add broccoli flowerets; stir-fry for about 5 minutes. Add the chicken; toss lightly, then remove from heat.

title: white pizza
directions: Make on any type of pizza dough.
Spread sour cream on first, then add Monterey Jack and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with onion cut in rings and black olives.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and basil on. Finally top with Parmesan cheese.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons olive oil on top and bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add all of the rest of the ingredients.
The amount of sugar can be less, according to your taste.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: pizza
directions: Heat broiler oven.
Cut cheese with star cookie cutter.
For each serving, spread muffin with ketchup, top with wieners and relish.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Broil until hot.
Top with cheese and broil until melted.

title: tomato sauce
directions: In a frypan, place the cooking oil.
Add celery, onions and green
peppers.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add flour, cloves, sugar, cinnamon, bay leaves and ketchup.
Mix well.
Add water and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling point; boil 5 minutes or until thick, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer another 5 minutes, stirring to prevent scorching.
Serve with spaghetti, meat balls, fish,
veal
and pork.
Makes approximately 1/2 to 3/4 of a gallon.

title: lorna doone dessert
directions: Mix crushed Lorna Doone cookies and melted butter to form crust. Pat into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Cool. Mix pudding and milk. Fold in softened ice cream and pour on top of crust. Chill at least 3 hours. Top with Cool Whip. Crush Heath candy bars and sprinkle on top of Cool Whip.

title: shell puffs
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil in a heavy saucepan.
Add flour and salt all at once, stirring vigorously with a wooden spoon until mixture forms a smooth ball and leaves the sides of the pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: white salad
directions: Heat marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Remove from heat. Add cream cheese which has been softened to room temperature. Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Cherries or other fruit may be added for decoration.

title: delicate lemon squares
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 3/8 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Press evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf(children's favorite)
directions: Soften bread or oats in milk.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into a loaf shape.
Place in a greased baking pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine and add cocoa. Add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. (Beat mixture really well after each egg.) Add canned milk and vanilla. Stir well. Pour into an unbaked pie crust. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: roasted peppers
directions: Slice peppers into 4 quarters; broil until skin is almost black.
Put peppers in a brown paper bag and shake.
Remove skin, soak in olive oil and season to taste.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add other ingredients and mix well. Shape into sandwiches.
Bake about 10 minutes in a 400° oven. Take out and roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Do not grease the baking sheet.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Insert dough hooks in electric mixer.
Set aside 1 cup flour. In large bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine at speed 3.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
Turn to speed 2; allow mixer to knead for additional 4 minutes.
Roll dough to 14 x 10-inch rectangle; place on greased baking sheet.
Spread dressing down center third of length of dough.
Top with layers of beef, cheese and sauerkraut.
Cut 1-inch wide strips along sides of filling out to dough edges.
Alternating sides, fold strips at angle across filling.
Cover with Saran Wrap; place over large shallow pan half filled with boiling water for 15 minutes.
Brush with egg white; sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly; serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Reheat to serve.

title: tropical cream pie
directions: Beat pudding mix with milk.
It will be thick.
Add pineapple, coconut, walnuts, cherries and almond flavoring and stir.
Add Cool Whip. Pour into crust and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, onion and tomatoes in big bowl.
Add cheese. Break up chips.
Add dry seasoning to hamburger and stir well. Add hamburger and beans to lettuce.
Toss and serve.
Best when hot.
Serve with taco sauce or favorite salad dressing.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and buttermilk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add oil and eggs.
Blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Batter can be baked immediately or stored in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Grease muffin cups or line with paper baking cups. Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 to 30 muffins.

title: real italian thick pizza(campania)
directions: This pizza is what my Mom
use to say is the real pizza of Italy.
It was served in
our home when we were growing up. As we got older and seeing American pizza, we wanted different toppings on our pizza.
Mom would
always
let
us make one or two with "our toppings".
As
I
have
gotten older, my tastes have changed and I prefer
the
plain
pizza
of
my heritage. This pizza was a real family favorite on New Year's Eve.

title: baked ham glaze
directions: Slice ham and grill.
Mix Coke, brown sugar, honey and syrup together.
Pour over grilled ham.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add some water if needed.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook slow in iron skillet until thick.	Pour into baked pie shell; top with meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mix squash and other ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain. Stir-fry in margarine and garlic.
Mix in tomato paste, salt, pepper, sour cream and cottage cheese.
In buttered casserole dish, spread a layer of mixture and a layer of cooked noodles twice and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cheese has melted.

title: tara's cream delight
directions: Soften cream cheese, then place in a medium bowl.
Mix all ingredients together until they become firm.
Then chill for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place in mold and serve with crackers.

title: onion garlic bubble bread
directions: Divide dough into 24 pieces. In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Dip each piece of dough into butter mixture and place in a 10 inch fluted tube pan coated with nonstick cooking spray. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: "house" salad dressing
directions: Beat all on low speed in blender until well blended.

title: gobbler burgers
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients; shape into 4 patties. Microwave, uncovered, at High for 7 minutes, turning patties once.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except 1/2 stick melted oleo and crushed corn flakes, in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with remaining oleo and corn flakes.
(Total of 1 stick oleo for the whole recipe.)
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Into a mixing bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add margarine and cut into dry ingredients, using pastry blender or 2 knives.
The mixture should have the texture of very coarse corn meal when it has been combined.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in greased 2-quart casserole, stems toward center.
Combine eggs, ham, milk and cheese soup and pour over broccoli.
Combine crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle on top. (Optional.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine shrimp, cream cheese, onions and mayonnaise.
Add green onions and the rest of ingredients to taste.
Blend in food processor or blender until well blended.
Chill a few hours before serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Soak poppy seed in milk 1 to 3 hours.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shrimp, in large mixing bowl, until light and well combined.
Add shrimp.
Heat mixture for about 2 or 3 minutes until warm.
Serve with chips and crackers or warm bread.

title: fudge
directions: Mix
sugar, milk, marshmallows, margarine and salt in a heavy 2 quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbling all over).
Boil and stir 5 minutes
more.
Remove
from heat.	Stir in until completely melted 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Add nuts and vanilla and stir well.
Spread in a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool. Cut into 30 pieces.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all together and press into 9-inch pie pan.

title: low-fat mozzarella in carozza
directions: Heat ironstone skillet (no stick).
Beat egg and milk.
Place cheese between the two slices of bread.
Dip edges first, then both sides in egg milk mixture.
Place in skillet until golden brown on both sides.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix
margarine	and
flour; add pecans.
Spread and pat out in	a large rectangular Pyrex dish or aluminum pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 300°.
Cool completely.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Wash nuts to remove salt, if salted nuts are used.
Set aside about 1/2 cup Chinese noodles for topping.
Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frances' fruitcake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing.
Sift about 1 cup of the flour over fruits and nuts, tossing to coat well.
To remaining flour, add baking powder. Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in lemon extract, then add fruit-nut mixture.
Grease, then line with brown paper, a deep tube pan and a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Lightly grease the paper. Spread batter into the 2 pans.

title: zesty barbecued pork
directions: In a regular-size oven cooking bag, place flour; shake to coat inside.
Add pork and remaining ingredients.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Press bag several times to mix well.
Make a small slit in bag near tie.
Place bag in a microwave-safe, shallow, 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 30 minutes, rotating dish a half turn after 15 minutes.

title: holly cookies
directions: Heat marshmallows and oleo over low heat.
Add coloring.
Add vanilla and corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Shape as holly wreath.
Put 3 red hot candies on each.

title: artichoke niblets
directions: Saute green onions in oil from artichoke jars.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together and spread in long glass Pyrex pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Take 2 scoops of strawberry ice cream, put it in the blender with a cup of milk and turn it on.
Stop when it is frothy.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, remove from pan and cook the onion and garlic until tender, then drain.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a large casserole.
Add the crumbled bacon, onion and garlic.
Stir well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler 2
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar, and milk together.
Pour into baking dish.
Pour peaches on top of that and bake at 350 for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix moist ingredients.
Fold together and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Look up the scriptures in the Bible to find the ingredients.
(Based on King James version.)

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper and egg.
Mix well.
Pat out to
12-inch
on wax paper.
Cube
bread.
Combine
with cheese, mushrooms and onion.
Spread mixture on meat to within 1-inch of edge.
Roll meat around
stuffing.
Press
to
seal. Place seam side down and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: picciadillo
directions: Brown ground beef with olive oil.
Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes in 1/4-inch cubes and then fry in deep fat.
Drain.
After beef is brown, add all the other ingredients.
Potatoes are added last. Serve over cooked rice.

title: magic pie
directions: Melt the margarine.
Mix in the sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into buttered pan; do not stir.
Add the fruit on top; still don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Blend or mix together in mixing bowl.
Slightly lumpy is okay. Use a ready made graham cracker pie crust.
Pour mixture into pie plate.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.
Cool overnight.
Use one can of Thank You brand blueberries over top.
Add Cool Whip, then serve.

title: chewies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time. Gradually add flour, vanilla, nuts and chips.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in greased pan.

title: american spaghetti
directions: Cut bacon into bite size pieces.
Dice onion and saute with bacon.
Do not drain.
When bacon is brown, add soup, water, salt and pepper.
Cook on medium for 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and add to sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes royale
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with coconut.
Arrange marshmallows on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until marshmallows are golden.

title: ricotta roll-ups
directions: Melt butter; add Ricotta and egg yolks and last the flour. Mix well until it forms a soft ball and all ingredients are mixed.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine the first three ingredients with cooked chicken breasts and simmer.
Layer over salsa chips, crushed, in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: tuna ball
directions: Make ball.
Roll in chopped pecans or parsley.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Melt in microwave.
Combine cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, nuts and vanilla.
Spread into pan and bake 12 minutes.
Remove and pour caramel mix over and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake 20 minutes or more at 350°. Cool and cut into squares.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Pare apples; slice into a bowl.
Mix sugar, spices and salt. Combine with the sliced apples.
Arrange apple mixture in unbaked shell.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 400° oven for 50 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Line pan with foil and grease with oleo and melt in 350° oven. Mix egg, water and salt.
Dip chicken in potato flakes, then in egg mixture, then in pan, skin side down, and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn pieces over and cook 35 to 40 minutes or more until done.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.	Add pecans.
Mix together sugar, salt and cinnamon.	Add pecans and mix until nuts are coated.
Place on foil-lined jelly-roll pan and bake 1 hour at 235°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: death by chocolate dessert
directions: Crumble 1/2 of the brownies in large bowl.
Top brownies with 1/2 of the chocolate mousse.
Top mousse with 1/2 of Cool Whip. Crumble 2 Heath bars and 1/2 of pecans on top of Cool Whip.
Repeat all steps and refrigerate overnight.

title: homemade lone bologna
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fill salt bag.
Tie up tightly; boil in kettle of hot water for 1 1/2 hours.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a bowl mix soup, milk, onion and mustard.
In a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread drained sauerkraut.
Top with uncooked noodles.
Spoon soup mixture evenly over noodles. Crumble corned beef over this.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of this.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: potato au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes until almost done; salt to taste.
Place in 9 x 20-inch baking dish.

title: top of the world chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts in 2 cups lightly salted water until tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into medium pieces. Blend mayonnaise and peach juice until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add diced chicken and peaches and gently stir until blended.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce or Romaine.

title: fruity winter salad
directions: Combine pineapple, bananas, grapes, dates or raisins and nuts. Arrange fruit on lettuce lined plates.
Top with favorite dressing.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: orange cranberry strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and frozen orange cranberry relish.
Stir until melted.
Add crushed pineapple; stir.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: vanilla extract
directions: Place the vanilla bean in the liqueur and let stand for 1 to 2 months.
This makes an exceptional extract and will enhance any recipe.
It is a strong vanilla so use less of it to taste.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix until dough is soft.
Spoon into well-greased 12-cup muffin tin.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape into ball.
Roll in 1/2 cup pecans.
Make the night before and let season overnight in the refrigerator.

title: stuffed jalapeno
directions: Fill jalapeno peppers with cheese.
Wrap peppers in bacon. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Generously salt, pepper and put garlic powder on top and bottom of tenderloin.
Leave out of refrigerator on broiling pan until it is room temperature (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: peanut butter scotchies
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add peanut butter and eggs; mix well.
Blend in vanilla and corn syrup.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine baking soda and oats.
Add to sugar mixture. Mix well.
Blend in chocolate and butterscotch pieces and nuts. Drop by scant tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Using knife, spread each cookie into circle.
Bake at 350° 8 to 10 minutes.

title: 300 dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar and cream to soft ball stage (6 to 10 minutes). Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until smooth and pour into buttered pan.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix hot water, Jell-O and sugar together until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add all other ingredients except ginger ale and sherbet. Add these when ready to serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and pack in a glass oblong baking dish the cake mix, egg and margarine.
Beat softened cheese until smooth.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add confectioners sugar and beat until fluffy.
Pour over cake mixture and cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: southern fried quail
directions: Cut quail in half down center back and breast.
Soak for 15 minutes or more in buttermilk.
Add salt and pepper to self-rising flour in a plastic bag.
Add quail and shake until birds are well coated.

title: quick veal parmigiana(for 6)
directions: Brown veal patties.
Drain.
Pour 1/2 of spaghetti sauce in casserole dish.
Lay the patties on top of sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour remaining spaghetti sauce over patties. Top with 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes, until cheese has melted and is starting to turn a golden color.
Serve with green beans, tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add pumpkin, cinnamon and ginger.
Serve with gingersnaps (Sunshine is the best).
This makes a lot, so split it and freeze the rest until the next party!

title: alison morse's strawberry yogurt popsicles
directions: Note:
Need 12 (3 ounce) paper cups and 12 wooden sticks.

title: ooey gooey bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients with mixer, spread on as second layer.
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. confectioners sugar and 6 oz. chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.
Will not look done in center.
Make sure completely cool before cutting.
Better 2nd day.

title: chicken tortilla
directions: Heat chili, salt, sour cream, soup and olives (reserve a small amount for garnish) in a saucepan until thoroughly mixed.
Mix chicken and onion together.
Pour 1/2 sauce into chicken/onion mixture.
Use 1/2 of mixture to fill tortilla shells.
Sprinkle cheese on top and roll.
Pour remaining sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese and reserved olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pineapple colada
directions: Mix all well in blender.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 2-quart Corning Ware dish.
Add milk, sugar and flour to butter in a baking dish. Blend well.
Sprinkle cinnamon over dough.
Gently spoon peaches over dough.
Bake for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugarless peanut butter cookies(special diet)
directions: Shape into 1-inch balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake on ungreased pan for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes until veggies are tender.
Add soup and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Enjoy!

title: eggplant with yogurt
directions: Bake the eggplant in a 400° oven until tender.
Piercing the eggplant with a fork before baking will allow the bitter juices to come out.
Cool the eggplant by peeling it under running water. Chop the pulp coarsely.
Saute the chopped onion in oil slowly. Do not brown it.
Add seasoning and cook for about 2 minutes.
Add eggplant and simmer while stirring for a few minutes.
Put eggplant mixture into a bowl; add the yogurt and refrigerate. Excellent as an appetizer or a side dish.

title: beef-n-biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and
onion in large frying pan; drain excess grease.
Add
tomato
sauce,
pepper
and
garlic salt. Simmer while preparing
biscuits.	Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits.
Pull each biscuit apart to make 2 layers.
Press biscuit layers over
entire
bottom
and
sides
of
ungreased 9-inch square baking
pan
or
2-quart casserole.
Combine 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese (reserve
the rest for topping), sour cream and egg; mix well.
Remove
meat mixture from heat and stir in cheese mixture.
Spoon over dough.
Arrange remaining biscuit layers over
top
pinching
sides	together.
Sprinkle
with remaining Cheddar
cheese.
Bake
at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice as directed, omitting butter.
Cool.
Add scallions, peppers, olives, artichokes and almonds.
Combine marinade from artichokes with curry and mayonnaise.
Toss together. Refrigerate several hours.

title: shrimp divine dip(low-cal)
directions: Blend cream cheese with remainder of ingredients. Chill one hour or longer. This is a wonderful dip with crackers or veggies.

title: "old" corn meal pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and corn meal; mix well.
Add eggs.
Mix oleo, milk and vanilla.
Pour in pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 30 minutes longer.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in microwave or steamer with a small amount of water until slightly tender.
Drain.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; put into greased baking dish.

title: ham and cheddar rounds
directions: Blend the cheese and butter in mixing bowl.
Add flour and seasoning.
Work together until dough forms.
Mold a heaping teaspoonful of cheese dough around each ham cube.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in screw-top jar.
Tighten lid and shake vigorously to blend well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator. Shake before using.

title: sugar-free strawberry cake
directions: Take sheet cake pan, tear up angel food cake into small pieces.
Take 2 boxes of jello mix, add only boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Pour over cake.
Let set in refrigerator. Top with Cool Whip lite.

title: mama's sweet potato crisp
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, sugar, 3/4 stick margarine, milk and cinnamon. Put into greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix cornflakes, brown sugar and nuts. Spread on casserole. Cut up 3/4 stick margarine over topping. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot, pecan and raisin salad
directions: In a medium bowl, toss chopped apples with lemon juice.
Stir in carrots, raisins and pecans.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate 24 hours to blend flavors. Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: clam chowder
directions: Open fresh clams with their own juice and grind in meat grinder.
Grind potatoes, carrots, onions, bacon and tomatoes. Put in a large kettle.
Add 1 quart of water, thyme and pepper. Bring to a boil; simmer 1 hour.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Debone chicken after cooked.
Prepare dressing.
Mix soup, sour cream and onion.
Spread thin layer of dressing in bottom of baking dish.
Lay chicken pieces (bite-size) over dressing, then pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with remaining dressing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: moist garlic chicken
directions: Combine butter, garlic, garlic powder, and salt. In another bowl combine bread crumbs, cheeses, and pepper. Dip chicken in butter mixture, then coat with crumb mixture. Place in a 9 x 13 inch pan coated with nonstick cooking spray. Cover and bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes or until chicken juices run clear. Serve over pasta.

title: beignets
directions: Heat milk until almost boiling, stirring so as not to scorch. Place shortening and sugar in a big bowl; pour scalded milk over and stir until smooth and melted.
Cool to lukewarm, then add yeast; stir until dissolved.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Drain carrots and pour into big bowl.
Place onion and pepper rings on top.
In saucepan over medium heat combine rest of ingredients.
Stir with wire whisk until all ingredients are well dissolved and warmed.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly to cover all vegetables.
Cover and marinate overnight.
You can add more carrots as needed to marinate.
Keeps a week or so.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix well with remaining ingredients, except bread.
Chill.
When ready to serve, make a bowl out of the Hawaiian bread by cutting out the soft center portion, filling with dip.
Cut the bread that has been removed into bite size cubes to dip in the spinach mixture.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except olives and bacon.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered dish.
Top with slices of bacon (cut in half and rolled) and 1/2 cup sliced olives.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake(blue ribbon pound cake)
directions: In mixer, cream the sugar, oleo and cream cheese well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla.
At slower speed, add flour a little at a time.
Pour into a large, greased and floured stem pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mykey wall's sausage quiche
directions: Bake pie shell for 3 minutes at 400°, prick with fork and bake 5 minutes.

title: swedish cake and topping
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and then add baking soda, flour, vanilla and walnuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While cake is still warm, cover with topping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine in mixing bowl and mix well eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to zucchini mixture and stir until blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased pans (8-inch bread pans).
Bake 1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool on rack. Makes 2 loaves.

title: markus' punch
directions: Shake well.
At serving time, add 16 ounces chilled club soda. Makes 16 drinks (approximately 5 1/2 ounce cups).

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, cheese and seasonings. Arrange well drained broccoli in a large casserole dish (greased). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Spread chicken on top and sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over it and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Dot with margarine. Cook 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven until bubbly and hot throughout.
Serve hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved and butter melts.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs, vanilla extract and salt to mixture.
Stir well.
Pour filling into pastry shell and top with pecan halves.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Yield: One 9-inch pie.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: Chill all ingredients thoroughly.
Mix shrimp with other ingredients.
Serve with parsley or lemon wedges for garnish.

title: banana salad
directions: Blend ingredients and cook on medium-low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Cover pan and set aside to cool.
When completely cool, fold in one large Cool Whip.
Crush one can of peanuts.
Slice crosswise 4 ripe bananas.
Layer dressing, banana and peanuts until used up.
Refrigerate and serve soon.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: tracey's peanut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Set aside.
Beat powdered sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in cream cheese and then fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust and freeze.
Serve frozen with hot fudge sauce.

title: molasses cookies
directions: After mixing ingredients, form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in extra sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cream dreams (chilled fudge candy)
directions: Stir cheese until soft and smooth.
Blend sugar with cheese. Add melted chocolate to cheese and beat well.
Stir in vanilla, salt and nuts.
Press into well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Makes 36 squares.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet. Top with 1/2 cherry or nut.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage crescent rolls
directions: Cook sausage links according to the package directions.
Drain well and cool.
Separate crescent roll dough into triangles. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jessie's sausage stew
directions: Combine broth, 1 cup water, pepper, bay leaf and vegetables, except potatoes, in a 4-quart saucepot.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Add potatoes; cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Mix 2 tablespoons water with flour; stir into vegetables.
Add sausage; heat.
Add salt.
Top each serving with cheese.

title: orange dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Put cake mix, oil and nectar in mixing bowl and mix 2 minutes. Add one egg at a time, beating after each egg.
Place in oiled tube pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour or until cake tests done. Frost with following:

title: homemade fruit roll-ups
directions: Cover a cookie sheet with plastic wrap.
Drain the fruit well. Pour fruit into electric blender.
Blend until fruit is a fine puree.
Spread puree on plastic wrap as thinly as possible, making sure there are no holes and that the fruit does not touch the edges.
At 150°, leave the cookie sheet in the oven overnight or until fruit is dry.
Remove cookie sheet from the oven.
Starting at one end, roll up fruit and plastic wrap.
Make one giant roll or cut up.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased loaf pan in a 325° oven about 1 hour.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons oil in Dutch oven.
Cook 4 tortillas, garlic and cilantro until tortillas are soft.
Add onion, tomato puree and next 5 ingredients.
Boil and simmer for 30 minutes. Remove bay leaves.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Drain.
Place sliced potatoes and onion in a pot and boil until slightly tender, but firm. Layer in casserole dish potatoes, onion, ground beef and remaining potatoes and onion.
Combine 3 tablespoons flour and melted butter.
Add milk to make a white sauce.
Pour over casserole. Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs a little bit.
Mix flour in sugar well and then add to eggs and milk.
Melt margarine in flour mixture.
Mix well, then add coconut and mix well.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Cook on 350° until done.

title: magic pie crust
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over melted margarine.
Add fruit.
Bake in a 400° oven until crust rises to the top and browns.

title: easy bird feeders
directions: *Suet can be purchased from butcher.

title: spaghetti
directions: Put the noodles in the microwave.
That's makes them soft. Roll the meat for the meatballs; put it in the oven for 1 hour. Shake the sauce and put it on the spaghetti.
Then you eat it. That's all.

title: saddle tramp chili
directions: Brown bell pepper and onion in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add ground meat and brown.
Drain.
Add seasonings, tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans and simmer for 20 minutes.
I add 1 tablespoon of sugar to cut down on the acid from the tomatoes.

title: stuffed roast turkey
directions: Mix crumbs, rice, chopped onion and popcorn with water.
Add melted oleo and seasoning and mix well.
Stuff turkey firmly and sew up opening.
Bake in 350° oven until the popcorn pops and blows the ass out of the turkey!

title: jane's white fudge
directions: Mix well, and pour into butter dish.

title: country breakfast
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with bread.
Cook sausage, crumble and drain. Sprinkle over bread.
Beat eggs and mustard. Add Pet milk.
Pour over sausage. Top with cheese. Cover with foil. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and boil in water for 20 minutes and drain.
In a separate saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar, vanilla, maple syrup and salt.
Pour syrup mixture over sweet potatoes.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are well sweetened (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir lemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: kaki's original quiche
directions: Bake the pie
shell.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon and cheese.
Line
shell
with	bacon and cheese, then pour in mixture of other
ingredients.
Bake
at
425° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to
Bake until lightly brown on top. Let stand 20 minutes before serving.	Vary ingredients such as spinach, mushrooms or other vegetables or seafood.

title: mrs. lou holtz's spinach squares
directions: Place spinach in strainer.
Rinse under hot water to thaw. Then press out all water.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Cook on medium heat until onions are limp.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, bread crumbs and mushroom soup with 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese, the spinach and seasonings. Blend in the onion-mushroom mixture.
Place into 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes or until set in a 325°
oven.
Cut in squares to serve hot or refrigerate and cut smaller for cold hors d'oeuvres.

title: banana coffee bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one. Stir in bananas. Add flour to banana mixture. Mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 9 pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ralphie's cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine beef, water, onion, pepper, salt, eggs and bread crumbs to form small meatballs.

title: corn puff
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to measure 1 cup.
In saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour and pepper.
Add reserved liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Stir in corn and beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into corn mixture; pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato caramel
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/4-inch thick slices; deep fry until golden brown.
Layer bottom of baking dish with potatoes.
In saucepan, add butter and sugar with a little water.
Completely melt.
Add ginger and orange rind.
Cook until caramelized.
Dip fork into this mixture and drizzle over potatoes.
It's very good in the winter when it snows outside!

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Cook ground beef, pepper and onion. Drain. Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix everything in crock-pot. Cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: berry glace pie
directions: Simmer 1 cup berries and 3/4 cup water in a saucepan for 3 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons cornstarch and 1 cup sugar to berries. Cook until thick and clear (creamy).
Add 1 teaspoon lemon juice. Cool slightly.
Pour berry mixture over 1 1/4 cups to 2 cups fresh berries in baked pie shell.
Very good with blueberries, red and black raspberries and strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.
Best eaten first day.

title: guava jam
directions: Cook
the
Guava
paste
and
sugar over medium to high heat, until boiling.
Then add the butter and Sure Jell.	Pour into pint jars.
Makes about 6 pints of jam.

title: russian meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll into meatballs.
Cook over medium heat until well browned.
Deep fry over medium heat until well browned or bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: steaks polynesian
directions: Brown steaks quickly in butter in large skillet.
Add onions, peppers, salt and pepper.
Brown lightly.
Add pineapple including juice, soy sauce, brown sugar and ginger.
Heat.
Blend cornstarch and water into a smooth paste.
Remove meat, pineapple and pepper strips.
Stir cornstarch into liquid in skillet, stirring constantly until sauce thickens and clears.
Return meat, pineapple and peppers to skillet.
Serve with hot rice.

title: shredded yams\(new perry hotel)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and shred potatoes in gallon of water.
Add salt.
Drain and wash well.
Place in baking dish. Mix sugar, syrup and 1/2 cup water; cook until it makes simple syrup.
Add margarine.
Pour pineapple juice over potatoes, then syrup.
Cook 35 minutes or until they are transparent.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Blend flour, baking powder and salt; mix in syrup.
Add enough water to make a soft dough.
With hands spread dough out on floured surface and pat to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut lengthwise then widthwise to make 2 x 3-inch pieces.
Cut a diagonal slit in each piece for even cooking.
Deep fat fry in shortening until light brown.
Turn bread to brown other side.
Place on paper towels to absorb grease.
Cover and serve warm.

title: royal bibingka
directions: Beat eggs until light and creamy.
Add sugar gradually beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together. Beat dry ingredients alternately with coconut milk.
Pour batter into 29-inch layer cake pans that have been greased and lined with wilted banana leaves.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out pans and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Brush twice with margarine while baking.
When done, brush again with margarine and sprinkle with sugar.
Serve with freshly grated coconut.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Preheat grill.
Place ribs and 2 cups water in large soup pot. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies]
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork dipped in water. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle tops with sugar before baking if desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in baking dish. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over apples. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: green grape salad
directions: Mix all ingredients all together in a large bowl, then either mold or leave in dish.
Refrigerate.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet. Dip a glass into a bowl of sugar (bottom of glass) and smash cookie. Do each cookie this way, then go back and crisscross them with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
By teaspoonfuls, shape into balls and flatten. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool on racks.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.
May add coconut and raisins, gumdrops or M&M's.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Allow cream cheese to soften to room temperature.
Assemble blender.
Put eggs, cream cheese and sugar into blender container.
Cover and process at blend until smooth.

title: italian delight
directions: Cook beef in frying pan.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Place in greased casserole dish; cover with layers of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Stir together and heat in crock-pot until cheese is melted. Serve as a dip for nacho chips.

title: chocolate cupcakes(makes 24 cupcakes)
directions: Melt in a saucepan the margarine and chocolate chips.
Add nuts.
Mix together flour, vanilla, sugar and eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: ham and black-eyed pea soup
directions: Cook peas in broth and water. When half cooked add seasonings, veggies and ham. Right before serving, stir in lemon juice. Can be frozen. Makes 6 main-dish servings. Good on a cold, rainy day!

title: easy yeast bread
directions: Melt butter in loaf pan.
Pour 2/3 of the butter into a cup. Mix yeast, sugar and milk.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Pour into the loaf pan and pour the butter in the cup over the batter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot spinach hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Squeeze out liquid when draining spinach.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Freeze or refrigerate until ready to use.
Cook at 300° for about 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain well and put in greased 7 x 12-inch
pan.
Combine soup and cheese and cook until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.
Place over vegetables. Combine melted butter and flavoring with crumbs.
Place on top. Bake at 350° until light brown and bubbly.

title: holiday oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oats, raisins and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Add in order the oil, eggs and milk.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 10 to 12 minutes or just until light brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: dakota barbecue
directions: Cook chuck steak slowly in 1 1/2 cups water with 1 teaspoon salt for 2 hours (or shred meat and remove fat).
Add rest of ingredients, except Coke.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add Coke. Serve over French bread or hamburger buns.
Serves 8 or 10 people. Yum, Yum!

title: ham noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in ovenproof casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add chili powder, mushroom soup and tomato sauce; simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: black forest cheese cake
directions: Spread cookie crumbs on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan, coated with cooking spray.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese at high speed with
an electric mixer until fluffy, gradually adding sugar, beating well.
Gradually add egg substitute, mixing well. Add melted chocolate, cocoa and vanilla; mix until blended.
Stir in sour cream alternative.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Run knife around edge of pan to release sides.
Let cool on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.

title: meat casserole
directions: In skillet, cook hamburger or sausage, onion, salt and pepper until brown; drain and mix with soups.
Place in baking dish and cover with Tater Tots.
Bake until brown in moderate oven.

title: strawberry or peach dream
directions: Line a bowl with ladyfingers.
Sprinkle the strawberries with sugar; let them set until they make juice (mash them a little bit).
Fold strawberries into the Dream Whip according to the package directions.
Pour into the ladyfingers bowl; chill for at least an hour.

title: hot pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 300°
for 30 minutes in a casserole dish.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings into baking utensil.
Mix sugar and soy sauce; pour over wings and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until wings are done.
Nice to make during football season.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly.
Serve hot with chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: banana pineapple punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in cold water. Add juices. Mash bananas. Mix all together. Fill 6 freezer containers. Thaw 2 hours before serving. Use one bottom of lemon lime or ginger ale for each container.

title: dump cake
directions: Note:
Dump ingredients in, do not stir.

title: party sausages
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Taste and add a little bit of brown sugar, if needed.
Drain cocktail sausages.
Add to sauce. Double the sauce for large package of sausage.

title: summer soup
directions: In the blender container, put 1 can of undiluted tomato soup plus 1/2 can of water, vinegar and olive oil (or your favorite vegetable oil).
Add coarsely chopped cucumber, green pepper strips garlic cloves and black pepper.
Whirl until pureed.

Chop tomatoes in fine dice and hold separately a minute, then add 4 or 5 ice cubes to the blender and whirl until ice is mainly broken up. Serve in bowl with croutons and the diced tomatoes sprinkled on, right away.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool and then crumble it up.
Make pudding as directed and set to the side.
Layer the cake, pudding, bananas, pineapple, 1 carton Cool Whip, blueberry pie filling and then cherry pie filling.
Repeat layering process and top with small amount of coconut.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Put in punch bowl.
Add 1 bottle of lemon-lime soda, 1 bottle ginger ale.
Stir often with ladle while dipping to keep apricot nectar mixed in.
Add lemon-lime soda and ginger ale when ready to serve.
This is good for a slush too.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients except sugar.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours (2 1/4 hours in tube pan).

title: molded chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add enough water to reserved juice to measure 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat juice.
Soften gelatin in cold chicken broth; add hot juice, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Fold in chicken, pineapple, celery and green pepper. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or until mold is firmly set.

title: texas hot wiener sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 2 hours, stirring frequently.
I mash it up with a potato masher to break ground beef up. Freezes well.
(Divide it into small servings; then freeze it; a quick meal.)

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix graham crumbs and butter; press in pie pan and bake 20 minutes.
Mix milk, egg and juice; pour into cool pie shell.
Whip the cream and spread on top and sprinkle with almonds.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans, 8-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package except substitute pineapple for the water.
Stir flavorings or coconut into batter.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake as directed.
Cool layers 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Fill and frost layers, or frost rectangular cake with whipped topping.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Refrigerate any remaining cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly beat eggs.
Add hamburger, green pepper, etc.
Mix and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Put American cheese over top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: 4-minute fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to boil.
Stirring constantly, boil mixture for 4 minutes.
Add chocolate pieces and marshmallow cream.
Beat fudge until thickened.
Add nuts.
Pour in an 8 or 9-inch square pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: south american flan
directions: Prepare in a glass Pyrex dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend the first 3 ingredients with mixer until smooth in consistency.
Set aside.

title: preacher's cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients by hand.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Cool.

title: poppy seed-lemon loaf
directions: Grease and flour one 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or three 5 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Into medium-sized bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, nutmeg, ginger and salt.
Add poppy seed and blend well.
In another medium-sized bowl, beat egg, oil, buttermilk and lemon peel.
Add flour mixture and stir until blended.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix in bowl with hand.
Place small spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Cook for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixer bowl. Beat in egg, milk and shortening. Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Double the recipe if you want a 9 x 13-inch pan of cornbread.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
While cheese is melting, drain tomatoes.
(Keep juice as you may need it.)
After cheese is melted, add can tomatoes, chopped olives, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
If dip is too thick, add juice of tomatoes.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Drain and mash. Add first 5 ingredients and beat on medium speed until smooth.
Put in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sheath cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and flour together in a large bowl.
Heat butter, cocoa, water and shortening in saucepan until it reaches boiling point. Pour hot mixture over dry ingredients and add buttermilk with soda in it.
Add eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well. Pour batter into 11 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick beef chowder
directions: In large saucepan, stir tomatoes into celery soup; stir in undrained corn, parsley, and salt. Add frozen beef mixture. Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4-5 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Pour in large bowl.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: lumpia
directions: Put the ground pork (uncooked) in a very large mixing bowl. Using a food processor, cut up all of the listed vegetables, except frozen peas and carrots, into small bits.
Mix all of the chopped vegetables into the pork.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Last, add the peas and carrots.

Take one lumpia wrapper, which are very thin, and place mixture in a line about the thickness of your finger to one side of the wrapper, leaving about an inch on both sides to the edge of the wrapper.
The line of mixture should be not quite two finger lengths long.
Take the wrapper edge (left and right sides) of the pork line and fold it over to cover the end of the line.
Do this to both sides.
Now take the smallest side of the wrapper and cover the mixture tightly, rolling the mixture into the center of the wrapper all the way to the opposite edge.
Holes in the wrapper are ok.
Dip your finger tips into the bowl of water and gently rub them over the outer edge of the wrapper to seal the wrapper shut.
The lumpia should look like a very tall, skinny egg roll.
Twice as long and half as round. Roll all of the lumpia rolls before proceeding further.
Uncooked lumpia can be frozen and cooked later.

title: italian lunch loaf
directions: Slice small top off bread (like a pumpkin top).
Hollow out loaf by pulling off all the white bread so just the shell of crust remains with bottom intact.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut candy slices fine with floured scissors or knife.
Mix with 1/2 cup flour.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, folding in egg whites last.
Pour into flat buttered pan.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: original mini fun chips squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, salt and baking soda. Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in large fun chips. Spread batter in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan. Sprinkle top of batter with the mini fun chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool before cutting.
Makes 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: quick and easy chicken rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
